<SLUG> BC-Australia-Egypt-Wheat </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Australia clinches first wheat sale to Egypt mill project 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   CANBERRA, Australia (AP) _ The Australian Wheat Board on Monday
announced the first sale of wheat to a joint venture flour mill in
Egypt the board is working with.
	   The 55,000 metric ton shipment _ the first of a series planned
for the Five Star Flour Mill in Cairo _ will be loaded at the West
Australian ports of Geraldton and Kwinana early this month,
Australian Wheat Board chairman and mill director Trevor Flugge
said.
	   The Australian Wheat Board has a 30 percent stake in the
project.
	   Flugge said the sale was significant as it marked the beginning
of new opportunities for Australian wheat growers in the
international trade's biggest wheat market.
	   ``With an import requirement of 6.5 million (metric) tons, a
growing population and a rapidly changing and developing milling
industry, Egypt is an important part of AWB Ltd.'s export focus,''
he said.
	   ``For Western Australian grain producers, who export over 95
percent of their grain through the company, this represents a
secure market for an estimated 120,000 tons of premium quality
wheat each year.'' 	   
</TEXT>
