<HEADLINE>
Papua New Guinean leader to be first to greet Habibie 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   PORT MORESBY, Papua New Guinea (AP) _ Prime Minister Bill Skate
will become the first national leader to meet Indonesia's new
President B.J. Habibie on a four-day state visit this week.
	   Skate had originally planned to meet with deposed former
president Suharto, whom he supported during the recent Indonesian
crisis.
	   Habibie agreed to the state visit going ahead after talks at the
diplomatic level over the past week.
