<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Thailand-Hitler Potato Chips, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ad agency apologizes over using Hitler to sell potato chips with client whether to pull ad. 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: RECASTS and UPDATES with three grafs with agency discussing
<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ An advertising agency was consulting
with its client Monday to decide whether a controversial commercial
using Adolf Hitler to sell potato chips should be pulled from Thai
television.
	   Leo Burnett Bangkok, the Thai branch of the global ad agency,
has expressed regrets after Israeli diplomats said they found the
advertising campaign, which is confined to Thailand, disgusting and
insensitive.
	   An agency spokeswoman, Simone Wheeler, said that discussions
were under way Monday with the Thai client, Food Processing Co.
Ltd., on ``the future of the advertisement'' for X potato chips, a
brand aimed at Thai teenagers.
	   In a statement issued Sunday, the agency said it ``wishes to
apologize to any persons who may be offended by a recent television
commercial for a potato crisp that uses images of Adolf Hitler.''
	   It shows Hitler giving a Nazi salute and cuts to a woman whom
Leo Burnett said ``clearly wants to change his evil ways by casting
a voodoo spell over him as he eats the crisps.''
	   A Nazi swastika turns into the product logo as the
transformation is completed.
	   ``The commercial is targeted to Thai teen-agers and is designed
to communicate that the world would be a better place if happiness
ruled. It was never intended to offend and the agency apologizes to
anyone who finds it sensitive,'' the statement said.
	   The poster version, displayed on many of the motorized
three-wheeled taxis plying Bangkok, suggests that eating the chips
would transform Hitler into a fun-loving Charlie Chaplin character.
	   The agency said it ``acknowledges Hitler as one of history's
most despicable dictators and would never do anything to suggest
otherwise.''
	   Israeli Embassy officials were not available for comment.
	   Hitler fanned fanatical nationalism in Germany and unleashed
World War II in Europe, wreaking death across the continent. Six
million Jews and millions of other civilians he viewed as subhuman
were murdered. 	   
</TEXT>
