<HEADLINE>
Russian border guards detain North Korean fisherman 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russian border guards detained 13 North Korean
trawlers Monday suspected of illegal fishing in the Bering Sea in
the Russian Far East, a news report said.
	   The boats have been escorted to the regional center of
Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
	   The report didn't say how the trawlers managed to reach Russia's
waters, or how many people may have been on the boats. North Korea
is suffering from a deep famine, but tight border controls in the
totalitarian state make it extremely difficult to leave its
territory.
	   Many North Korean defectors are living illegally in Russia with
the hope of reaching capitalist South Korea.
