<SLUG> BC-Dollar-Gold </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dollar mixed; gold down 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ The U.S. dollar had a mixed performance against
other major currencies in early European trading Monday. Gold
prices fell.
	   Dollar rates compared with late Friday:
	   _ 1.7768 German marks, down from 1.7838
	   _ 139.54 Japanese yen, up from 138.50
	   _ 1.4785 Swiss francs, down from 1.4808
	   _ 5.9580 French francs, down from 5.9821
	   _ 2.0030 Dutch guilders, down from 2.0110
	   _ 1,751.50 Italian lire, down from 1,757.9
	   _ 1.4573 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4545
	   The British pound was quoted at dlrs 1.6325, up from dlrs
1.6295.
	   London dealers fixed a recommended gold price of dlrs 292.35 per
ounce at midmorning, down from the closing price of dlrs 293.10 bid
Friday.
	   In Zurich the bid price was dlrs 292.25, down from dlrs 293.25
late Friday.
	   Earlier in Hong Kong, gold fell 30 cents to close at dlrs 292.65
bid.
	   Silver opened in London at dlrs 5.10 bid troy ounce, up from
dlrs 5.07 bid Friday.
	   (mj)
</TEXT>
