</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Miners </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Miner dies, two others injured in Ukraine 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ One miner died and two others were injured
when a layer of rock collapsed in a coal mine in the eastern
Ukrainian region of Donetsk, officials said Monday.
	   The accident occurred at the Korotchenko mine on Sunday, and the
wounded were hospitalized, the Emergency Situations Ministry said.
	   Mine officials have launched an investigation into the accident.
	   The death brought to more than 165 the number of miners killed
on the job this year and highlighted the crisis in the Ukrainian
mining industry, which is suffering from poor work conditions and
lack of funding.
	   Dozens of mines were idled by scattered strikes last month as
workers demanded payment of back wages, salary hikes and more state
support for the struggling industry.
	   (ms/sms/mr) 	   
