<HEADLINE>
Yemen executes convicted murderer in public square 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   SAN`A, Yemen (AP) _ A man convicted of murder and robbery was
executed in a public square in southern Yemen, al-Thawra newspaper
reported Monday.
	   Fayez Ahmed al-Faqeeh was executed Sunday by firing squad in the
main square in the city of Ibb, 300 kilometers (185 miles) south of
the capital San`a, the government-run newspaper said.
	   Al-Faqeeh shot Ali Mohammed Aamel last November with an assault
gun and robbed him, the paper said.
	   The execution was attended by a large crowd including Aamel's
family, the paper reported.
	   Yemen, an impoverished country at the tip of the Arabian
Peninsula, applies the death penalty for rape and murder. Most
executions are carried out in public to set an example.
