<SLUG> BC-Greece-Summer Hours </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Staggered work hours begin in Athens 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ In its annual effort to reduce rush-hour
traffic and summer pollution, the government began staggered
working hours Monday.
	   Under the new hours, which end Sept. 30, public services open at
7 a.m., banks at 7:45 a.m., supermarkets at 8 a.m. and all other
shops by 9 a.m.
	   The sultry summer weather in Athens elevates smog levels, often
to degrees considered dangerous to health.
	   A partial ban on cars in central Athens is scheduled to be
lifted Aug. 3-23 because of fewer drivers in the capital during the
peak vacation period for Greeks.
