<SLUG> BC-Somalia-Bus Attack </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Somali gunmen kill four bus passengers in Mogadishu 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   MOGADISHU, Somalia (AP) _ Gunmen killed four people and wounded
five others in an attack Monday on a bus in south Mogadishu,
witnesses said.
	   An armed guard on the bus returned fire, they said. The bus
driver and conductor were seriously wounded, and were taken to a
nearby hospital.
	   The attack may have been in retaliation for the robbery of
another bus last week by subclansmen of the owner of the bus that
was hit Monday, witnesses said, speaking on condition of anonymity.
	   In a separate incident also in the south of the capital, gunmen
on Saturday abducted a Somali working for the French aid group,
Action Against Hunger, aid workers said.
	   Sheikh Omar Awdhegle, who is responsible for the financial
affairs of the agency in Mogadishu, also was abducted in September,
but was released unharmed two days later.
	   Somali has not had central government since the 1991 overthrow
of dictator Mohamed Siad Barre. The country is divided up into
clan-based fiefdoms and kidnappings are a common way of extorting
money.
	   Ten Red Cross workers were held hostage for 10 days in the north
of the capital in April before being released unharmed.
	   (aan-kjd)
</TEXT>
