<HEADLINE>
BANGLADESH
</HEADLINE>
Zia's contribution recalled, THE INDEPENDENT  
   xfdws ZIA'S-CONTRIBUTION sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   BNP Standing Committee member and former minister Dr Khandker
Mosharraf Hossain yesterday urged the people to make June 9 long
march a success for protecting the sovereignty of the country and
foiling ``conspiracy'' to surrender over one tenth of the land of
the country.
	   He was speaking as chief guest at a discussion meeting on the
17th anniversary of death of late president and founder of the
Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP) Shaheed Ziaur Rahman organised
by Bangladesh Jatiyatabadi Mohila Dal Dhaka city unit at the BNP
central office.
	   Presided over by BNP joint secretary general Begum Selima
Rahman, the meeting was attended by Begum Shamsunnahar Khawaja
Ahsanullah special guest.
	   Begum Rabeya Siraj, Shirin Sultana, Advocate Khaleda Panna,
Feroza Talukdar and Prof Shahriar Akhter Bulu spoke among others.
	   Dr Khandker Mosharraf Hossain said Zia was a successful soldier,
politician and nation-builder. He said Zia not only announced
independence but also built up a self-reliant economy changing the
image of the bottomless basket. He said Zia had introduced the
politics of production in the country.
	   He said through Bangladeshi nationalism Zia ensured the national
identity of the people of the country. He said the present ruling
party was also following the free market economy which Zia had
first introduced in the country.
	   Selima Rahman said a conspiracy against the country's
independence and sovereignty was going on. She urged the people to
unitedly foil the conspiracy.
	   Begum Shamsunnahar Khawaja Ahsanullah said Zia ensured the
freedom of press.
	   
</TEXT>
