<HEADLINE>
Four European-based players among Tunisia's World Cup squad sted five 
</HEADLINE>
EDS: repeating to CORRECT headline to four European-based players
<TEXT>
	   TUNIS, Tunisia (AP) _ Tunisian coach Henri Kasperczak on Monday
announced his squad for the World Cup, including four
European-based players he hopes will give the team vital
international experience.
	   It will be the second time Tunisia has played in a World Cup,
coming 20 years after its debut in Argentina. Many observers say
the current squad is the most talented Tunisia has ever fielded.
	   Kasperczak, from Poland, chose four players from European
leagues: striker Adel Sellimi of Spanish second division team Jaen;
the Freiburg (Germany) duo of Zoubeir Beya and Mahdi Ben Slimane;
and France's Bastia goalkeeper Ali Bou Mnijel.
	   Tunisia is in the same group as Romania, England and Colombia.
	   The squad:
	   Goalkeepers: Chokri Ouaer (Esperance sportive tunisien,), Ali
Boumnijel (Bastia, France,) Radhouane Essalhi (Etoile sportive du
Sahel, ESS).
	   Defenders: Tarek Thabet (Esperance), Khaled Badra (Esperance),
Farid Chouchane (ESS), Mounir Boukadida (ESS), Sami Trabelsi (Club
sportif sfaxien, CSS), Jose Clayton (ESS), Hatem Trabelsi (CSS),
Sabri aballah (Club africain, CA).
	   Midfielders: Kaies Ghodbani (ESS), Siraj Eddine Chihi
(Esperance), Riadh Ouazizi (ESS), Zoubeir Baya (Freiburg), Skander
Souayah (CSS), Faycal Ben Hmid (Esperance).
	   Strikers: Imed Ben Younes (ESS), Mahdi Ben Slimane (Freiburg,
Germany), Riadh Jlassi (ESS), Mourad Malki (Olympique), Adel
Sellimi (Jaen, Spain).
	   (parf-ip)
</TEXT>
