<TEXT>
	   Workers Party of Bangladesh has called upon the democratic and
non-communal forces to build up strong resistance against the
``anti-people measures'' of the ruling Awami League which, it said,
had miserably failed to run the government.
	   The party yesterday announced a series of agitation programme on
the basis of an eleven-point charter of demands that was finalised
in the party central committee meeting on Friday.
	   According to the programme, Workers Party will stage
country-wide demonstration on June 15 and organise a fortnight
agitation programme throughout the country between July 1 and 15.
	   Announcing the programme at a press conference in the city,
party General Secretary Rashed Khan Menon called upon the
democratic non-communal forces to unite and take active part in the
movement for restoration of peoples power.
	   Criticising the failure of the government, Rashed Khan Menon
said all the election pledges made by Awami League had turned to be
hoax within two years of rule. The overall crisis had deepened due
to their inefficiency in managing the state affairs particularly
the economy of the country.
	   
