<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Tajikistan-Floods </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Floods cause damage in Tajikistan 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Floods caused by heavy rains damaged or destroyed
350 homes in the Central Asian country of Tajikistan, submerged
floodlands and caused an irrigation system to collapse, a news
agency reported Monday.
	   Farmland in southern Tajikistan was worst hit by the flooding
Sunday, deputy prime minister Ismat Eshmirzoyev told ITAR-Tass.
	   But in the northern Kanibadam region, 350 houses were damaged or
destroyed, an irrigation station collapsed and a water pumping
station broke, allowing hundreds of hectares (acres) of crops to be
submerged.
	   (ls)	   
</TEXT>
