w2650  wstm-
r w     BB-TREASURY-BILLsked     06-01 0266
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BB-TREASURY-BILL sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BANGLADESH
</HEADLINE>
BB treasury bill auction results, THE INDEPENDENT  
   xfdws BB-TREASURY-BILL sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   The 96th auction of the 90-Day Treasury Bill, the 87th auction
of the 30-Day and the 180-Day Treasury Bills and the 61st auction
of the l-year Treasury Bill were held Sunday.
	   Forty eight bids for a total of Tk 454 crore of 30-Day Bill,
three bids for a total of Tk 20 crore of 90-Day Bill, one bid for
Tk five crore of 180-Day Bill and 48 bids for a total of Tk 322.50
crore of l-year bill were offered.
	   Of these, 18 bids for a total of Tk 242.90 crore of 30-Day Bill
and 33 bids for a total of Taka 247.50 crore of 1-year Bill were
accepted.
	   The bids offered for the 90-Day and 180-Day bills were not
accepted.
	   The weighted average prices of the accepted bids against the
30-Day and l-year bills were Tk 99.30 and Tk 90.70 per 100 Taka
respectively.
	   The corresponding yields are 8.43 per cent and 10.25 per cent
per annum.
	   
</TEXT>
