<TEXT>
	   A FIRE believed to have been caused by an electrical
short-circuit razed a flat in Ho Man Tin Estate early Sunday
morning.
	   Two men were injured _ one while jumping from the third-floor
flat to the ground to escape the flames and the other from smoke
inhalation.
	   Both victims, aged 48 and 49, were in stable condition at Queen
Elizabeth Hospital on Sunday night.
	   The fire was reported at 2.40 am and put out by firemen about
half an hour later. Damage to the flat was extensive.
	   According to sources at the scene, the third-floor flat was
rented by a congee stall owner to serve as a dormitory for its
workers. The shop is located on the ground floor.
	   The Housing Department is investigating whether the tenant had
violated terms of its agreement with the department.
	   
