<HEADLINE>
BANGLADESH
</HEADLINE>
DSE remains on gaining track, THE INDEPENDENT  
   xfdws DSE-REMAINS-ON-GAINING sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   The All Share Price Index of the Dhaka Stock Exchange (DSE) rose
for the seventh consecutive day Sunday .The number of losers and
gainers are almost equal .
	   All Share Price Index climbed by 1.62 per cent or 10.08 points.
	   However, a few companies of high market capitalisation- like
Singer Bangladesh Ltd, Bangladesh Lamps Ltd, BATBC Ltd, Chittagong
Cement Clinker and Bata Shoe Company Ltd- had excellent performance
on the day.
	   If those companies were included in the minus column, the price
index of the day would have been quite different.
	   Both the sellers and the buyers had equal influence on the DSE
floor yesterday , DSE dealer Jamil Ahmed Khan said.
	   The day's price index rose to 628.18 points from previous day's
618.10 points.
	   The gainers of the day declined to 61 and the losers increased
to 62 from previous day's 127 and six respectively, while the total
number of securities changed hands yesterday stood at 125. Two
issues remained unchanged in their share value.
	   The volume of the day marked a rise by 1,57,422 shares and
debentures to the day's 4,71,813 from 3,14,391 shares and
debentures of Saturday.
	   At the same time, the value marked a rise by Taka 13.63 million
in the yesterday's transactions, to close at Taka 42.34 million
from the previous day's Taka 28.71 million.
	   The market capitalisation rose by Taka 0.90 billion to Taka
56.49 billion from Saturday's Taka 55.59 billion.
	   Prominent gainers of the day for trading the single share were:
Singer Bangladesh Ltd by Tk 218.75, Bangladesh Lamps Ltd by Tk
124.46, Chittagong Cement Clinker by Tk 74.11, Aziz Pipes Ltd by Tk
45.50, Islami Bank Bangladesh Ltd by Tk 39.00, Apex Tannery Ltd by
Tk 33.39, Monno Ceramic Industries Ltd by Tk 33.37, GQ Ball Pen
Industries Ltd by Tk 24.65, Aftab Automobiles Ltd by Tk 19.99,
Usmania Glass Sheet Factory Ltd by Tk 19.94, Olympic Industries Ltd
by Tk 17.40, Atlas Bangladesh Ltd by Tk 17.10, Eastern Cables Ltd
by Tk 16.42, Confidence Cement Ltd by Tk 13.49, Apex Footwear Ltd
by Tk 11.10 and Green Delta Insurance Co Ltd by Tk 10.00.
	   On the other hand, prominent losers of the day were: Delta Life
Insurance Ltd by Tk 66.90, National Tubes Ltd by Tk 46.61, Apex
Foods Ltd by Tk 44.88, Amam Sea Food Industries Ltd by Tk 42.27,
Square Pharmaceuticals Ltd by Tk 37.00, United Leasing Company Ltd
by Tk 18.18, Kay  Que Ltd by Tk 17.51, AMCL Pran by Tk 17.31,
Niloy Cement Ltd by Tk 16.77, Libra Pharmaceuticals Ltd by Tk
15.93, 5th ICB Mutual Fund by Tk 12.00, Bangas Ltd by Tk 10.88,
Uttara  Finance Investment Ltd by Tk 10.43, Phoenix Insurance Ltd
by Tk 10.25, 3rd ICB Mutual Fund by Tk 10.00 and Pragati Insurance
Ltd by Tk 10.00.
	   
