<HEADLINE>
HONG KONG
</HEADLINE>
Illegal CDs seized in `Terminator' raid, HONGKONG STANDARD  
   xfdws 'TERMINATOR'-RAID sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   CUSTOMS officers on Sunday raided shops in a Tsuen Wan shopping
centre, seizing more than 30,000 suspected pirated CDs and CD-roms.
	   Four men, aged 15 to 39, were arrested in the operation
code-named Terminator. They were later released on $5,000-$10,000
bail.
	   A spokesman for the Customs and Excise Department said on Sunday
31,331 items including video CDs, music CDs, TV games CD-roms and
computer software CD-roms worth almost $1 million were seized from
four shops in Nam Fung Centre.
	   The spokesman said $31,000 worth of paraphernalia was also
seized from the shops.
	   ``This is the fifth consecutive operation mounted against shops
in shopping arcades selling infringing compact discs since 27 May
this year,'' the spokesman said.
	   ``The operation is aimed at suppressing piracy activities by
crippling the retail business of shops selling infringing compact
discs, and computer software,'' he added.
	   
