<TEXT>
	   Health and Family Welfare Minister Salahuddin Yusuf yesterday
urged the physicians to provide proper services to heart patients
in rural as well as urban areas, reports BSS.
	   ``We should extend our services to the rural areas as a lot of
people are suffering from heart diseases there,'' he said while
inaugurating a five-day national cardiology workshop at the
National Institute of Cardiovascular Diseases (NICVD) here.
	   The minister said all physicians should be sincere and dedicated
to provide services to the patients within limited resources.
	   He said the present government has increased facilities in
different medical colleges in the country for providing proper
treatment and diagnosis of the disease. ``Some doctors and nurses
of medical college hospitals are imparted training in this
regard,'' he said.
	   The minister urged the doctors of different thana health
complexes to create awareness among the patients in the rural areas
saying the rural people are not well aware about it.
	   He underscored the need for introducing more modern facilities
in the NICVD to stop the tendency of going abroad by a section of
well-to-do people for treatment.
	   State Minister for Health and Family Welfare Dr M Amanullah,
Prof M Akhtaruzzaman, Director NICVD, and Professor of cardiology,
of NICVD M Jalaluddin also addressed the inaugural session.
	   At least 35 doctors from different health centres are
participating in the workshop.
	   
