<TEXT>
	   THE Action Committee for Defending the Diaoyu Islands is looking
for volunteer sailors to help them sail to the disputed islands.
	   The committee's 100 tonne ship, Diaoyu Tai, is scheduled to set
sail on 21 June and return after 10 days from the islands that are
claimed by China, Japan and Taiwan.
	   Group vice-chairman Tsang Kin-shing said they were looking for
volunteers to join up, including a boatswain, an engineer and other
veteran seafarers.
	   ``Because of the tight budget, we can only ask for volunteers,''
he said.
	   With departure day just three weeks away, the committee is still
trying to raise more funds.
	   The group, which backs China's claim to the islands, has raised
$100,000 to fund the trip but needs another $400,000.
	   As of yesterday, it had only raised $17,000 from the public. But
Mr Tsang said he was not worried.
	   ``There is still plenty of time,'' he said.
	   He said the group would continue its fund-raising activities
next week.
	   ``I hope people can come and support our mission,'' he said.
	   
