<TEXT>
	   To mark the 50th anniversary of India's independence
celebrations, a series of cultural programmes by Indian artistes
will be performed in Chittagong in the next month, reports BSS.
	   The first such programme is a Bharata Natyam dance to be
performed by famous dancer and dance writer Leela Samson at
Chittagong Club auditorium on June 3 along with her troupe, a press
release of the Assistant High Commissioner of India said.
	   One of Leela's attributes is her multi-dimesnional role as a
performer and teacher of Bharata Natyam, and as a writer she is
able to interpret the intricacy and feel of her style in an idiom
which is intelligible and sensitive.
	   She has performed at leading dance festivals in India and
abroad. A product of Kalakshetra, the college of fine arts founded
by Rukmini Devi Arundale, her work is recorded in a documentary
film ``Sanchari''. Ms Samson has been awarded with the Sanskriti
Award and the Padmashri Award, the press release said.
	   Ms Kumkum Dhar is another famous dancer, one of the finest
exponents of the Lucknow School of Kathak who will be performing in
Chittagong on June 10 at Chittagong Club.
	   Ms Dhar has performed in Canada, USA, UK, Egypt, Israel,
Pakistan and the Middle East. A doctorate in economics, she is also
a drama artiste and a vocal musical artiste of repute. She received
her training under the legendary Kathak Maestro Guru Lachhu
Maharaj, the press release added.
	   
