<SLUG> BC-Egypt-Libya, 1st-Ld Writethru,0250 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Gadhafi's trip to Egypt postponed overline 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: UPDATES with officials announcing trip delayed, CHANGES
<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ Libyan leader Moammar Gadhafi's visit to
Egypt that was scheduled to start Tuesday has been postponed
indefinitely, officials said Monday.
	   Gadhafi's trip is ``canceled for now,'' Omar Rashwan, Libya's
coordinator for affairs with Egypt, told reporters in the western
Egyptian town of Mersa Matrouh, where Gadhafi was to stop en route
to Cairo.
	   No explanation was given. However, the Libyan leader is known
for changing plans without notice. It could also be that his visit
was considered inconvenient at a time when Egypt is heavily
involved in trying to organize an Arab summit on Mideast peace.
	   No date for a new visit has been announced. An Egyptian
presidential official, speaking on condition of anonymity,
confirmed Gadhafi will not arrive Tuesday and that the trip was
``postponed to an indefinite date.''
	   Gadhafi was to arrive with a high-level delegation including
nine ministers and a team of businessmen to discuss boosting trade
relations and investments.
	   Gadhafi and Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak were scheduled to
meet Wednesday. Their talks were likely to touch on Libya's feud
with the West over the 1988 bombing of an American airliner.
	   The postponement caught Egyptian officials by surprise as many
of them were in meetings to prepare for the visit when the
announcement was made. 	   
</TEXT>
