<TEXT>
	   Six persons were killed and 30 injured in two separate road
accidents at Bhulta and Shahe Pratap on the Dhaka-Sylhet highway
this morning.
	   Three persons died on the spot and three others were seriously
injured when a Dhaka-bound bus from Bhagalpur hit two rickshaws
from behind at Shahe Pratap at about 7.30 am.
	   The rickshawpuller, Ekabbar (28) and two passengers - Monir
Hossain (40) and his mother Halima (70)- died on the spot.
	   Another rickshawpuller, Jalal Miah (27) and passengers Abul
Hossain (38) and Amena (12) were admitted to the Narsingdi Sadar
Hospital in critical condition.
	   Police seized the bus.
	   In another accident near Bhulta a Dhaka-bound minibus coming
from Monohordi skidded off the road as the driver lost his control
over the vehicle at about 11 am. Three persons died on the spot.
Two of them were identified as Nizam (16) and Shahidul (28) of
Kachikata village under Monohordi thana of Narsinghdi district.
	   The bodies of the victims were sent to the Narayanganj General
Hospital for autopsy.
	   The seriously injured, Noor Mohammad (21), Tajul Islam (35) and
Shah Jalal (25) were sent to Dhaka Medical College Hospital.
	   Others were treated at Araihazar thana health complex.
	   Separate cases were lodged with Narsinghdi Sadar and Narayanganj
thana.
	   
