two brotherly Muslim countries would be expanded in future and both
the countries will continue to work together for peace, progress
and happiness of their peoples.
	   Appreciating the leading role played by the Saudi Arabia for the
cause of Muslim Ummah, Justice Shahabuddin Ahmed reiterated
Bangladesh's total support to the struggle of the Palestinian
people and for their just cause.
	   Chairman of the Shoura Consultative Council Sheikh Muhammad Bin
Ibrahim Bin Jubair who led the delegation recalled with
satisfaction the development of cooperation between the two
brotherly countries and hoped that such cooperation would be
further expanded in future for the benefit of the peoples.
	   He said the Bangladeshis working in Saudi Arabia are not treated
as foreigners in the trust of sense of the term but they are
treated as brothers.
	   Saudi Ambassador to Bangladesh Abdullah Omar Barri was present
in the meeting.
	   
