<HEADLINE>
HONG KONG
</HEADLINE>
Appeal for witnesses to Kowloon East accidents, HONGKONG STANDARD  
   xfdws APPEAL-FOR-WITNESSES sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   POLICE in Kowloon East are appealing for witnesses to three
accidents in which three people died.
	   In the first, a motorcyclist died after crashing into a lorry on
Clear Water Bay Road on 2 May.
	   The 34-year-old lorry driver said he saw the motorcycle only
after hearing a crashing sound while approaching Choi Hung Estate
at 3.30 pm.
	   The 29-year-old motorcyclist and his 26-year-old female
companion were taken to United Christian Hospital where the man was
certified dead.
	   On 25 April, a 48-year-old woman passenger was killed when a
taxi collided with two other vehicles on Po Lam Road North near
Tseung Kwan O at 6am.
	   The taxi was travelling down Po Lam Road North when it ran into
a mid-size lorry and a car on the opposite lane.
	   All three taxi passengers and the car driver were injured and
rushed to United Christian Hospital, where the woman died.
	   A third accident, near Sai Kung Country Park on 21 April,
happened after two light goods vehicles were stopped by a police
officer on the northwest bound lane of Tai Mong Chai Road near Wong
Keng Tei about 5.45 am.
	   A third van attempting to overtake the two vans collided with
the first as it tried to get back to its lane.
	   The driver of the third van died four days later at Prince of
Wales Hospital.
	   Any witness may contact Kowloon East traffic division's special
investigation team 2 at 2305-7507 or 2754-7668 or the police
hotline at 2527-7177.
	   
</TEXT>
