<HEADLINE>
BANGLADESH
</HEADLINE>
Sharifa, Arif confess they abetted in Ruby murder, THE INDEPENDENT  
   xfdws SHARIFA-ARIF-CONFESS sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   Maidservant Sharifa and guard Arif who were arrested for their
alleged involvement in housewife Rubina Akhter Ruby murder case
yesterday made confessional statements in the court of the Chief
Metropolitan Magistrate, Dhaka.
	   Ruby (25) was murdered at her residence at Shantinagar in the
city on Friday last.
	   Maidservant Sharifa was arrested from her village home at
Shabazpur village under Sharail thana in Brahmanbaria district on
Saturday while guard Arif was arrested from Shantinagar on the day
of the incident.
	   Sharifa told the Magistrate that she abetted the main accused
Samad in killing Ruby. She said that she had an affair with Samad
since long and they had physical relation as well.
	   Sharifa stated that she was sacked and driven out from the house
by Rubina one and a half months ago when Samad proposed to her.
	   This incident infuriated them and they decided to kill Rubina,
Sharifa said. She added that she came to Dhaka to meet Samad two
days before the murder and went back home the same day.
	   Guard Arif confessed that Samad induced him by offering him cash
to assist him in killing Rubina. Arif added that Samad, guard
Emdadul Haq and he entered the apartment of Rubina by the balcony
and knocked the door. Rubina came out and Samad attacked her and
cut her throat with a boti'. The boti' was brought from Rubina's
kitchen, Arif said.
	   Metropolitan Magistrate Abdus Salam Mian recorded the
confessional statements of Sharifa and Arif from 12 noon to 5pm.
	   On recording the statements the Magistrate send them to the
jail.
	   The main accused Samad and Emdad were earlier arrested and they
are now remanded in police custody for seven days.
	   The case is being investigated by the Detective Branch (DB) of
police. Blood-stained clothes of the victim and the main accused
Samad have been sent for forensic test.
	   Meanwhile, teachers, students and employees of the Institute of
Cost Management and Accounting of Bangladesh (ICMAB) yesterday
brought out a condolence procession from the institute which
paraded the city streets and ended at National Press Club. They
demanded fair investigation of the murder of Rubina and exemplary
punishment to the culprits. Rubina was a student of the ICMAB.
	   
</TEXT>
