<HEADLINE>
BANGLADESH
</HEADLINE>
Woman gets life for abducting baby, THE INDEPENDENT  
   xfdws WOMEN-GETS-LIFE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   The Nari O Shishu Nirjatan Daman Bishesh Adalat, Dhaka yesterday
awarded life imprisonment to a 20-year old woman named Parveen
Akhter Munni on charges of abducting a baby and holding it to
ransom.
	   According to the case, Parveen Akhter Munni, a housemaid,
abducted a four-year old girl, Sumaiya Afroze Tamanna, from East
Nayanagar Fasher Tek area under Gulshan thana on February 12, 1996.
Munni took Tamanna to the Chittagong Export Processing Zone, (EPZ)
area and demanded one lakh 50 thousand Taka from Tamanna's father
as ransom.
	   Later, Kotwali police recovered Tamanna and arrested Parveen
Akhter Munni.
	   Delwar Hossain, father of Tamanna, filed a case with Gulshan
thana.
	   Judge Tapan Kumar Rudra of the special court after examining 12
witnesses found Parveen Akhter Munni guilty and her awarded life
imprisonment.
	   
</TEXT>
