<BODY>
<SLUG> OUTLAWS-INTENSIFY sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BANGLADESH
</HEADLINE>
Outlaws intensify activities in greater Rajshahi district, THE INDEPENDENT  
   xfdws OUTLAWS-INTENSIFY sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   Outlaws have intensified their activities in greater Rajshahi
district recently.According to reliable sources , the activists of
the outlawed Sarbahara Party, officially known as Purba Banglar
Communist Party (M-L), received a crushing blow in the hands of the
army and the then Rakkhi Bahini in Tanore and Atrai thanas of
greater Rajshahi district in 1974 in which about 100 extremists
were killed and another 100 injured.
	   The activities of the outlawed party stopped in greater Rajshahi
district since then and it turned its attention to the southern
districts of the country .The outlaws at a secret meeting in
Naogaon recently formed an organising committee comprising members
from Rajshahi, Naogaon and Natore districts . The committee has
also allegedly formed 'Killer Squads' in various thanas and unions
of the districts.
	   The members of the squads are mainly wanted criminals and
murderers.Rajshahi unit of the committee, through leaflets,
distributed in various village markets and hats recently, has
claimed the responsibility of killing Jubo League leader Lalu of
Naogaon in March last. The leaflets also claimed that the outlawed
party members also killed Abu Bakkar, chairman of Khajura Union
Parishad of Natore district in December last. Golap, a witness of
the Bakker murder case , was also allegedly killed by the activists
of the outlawed party.
	   Golap was called by some unidentified people from a tea-stall in
broad daylight and was killed by decapitating the head from the
body by sharp weapons at Birkutsa railway station during last
Ramzan. The people of these areas are passing their days in utter
panic . People of the areas do not dare come out of their homes
after dusk.It is alleged that the outlaws are sending letters to
the affluent people including political activists and farmers in
rural areas of Rajshahi, Naogaon and Natore districts demanding
huge sum of money from them.
	   They are also threatening them not to disclose the information
contained in the letters to police. The letters have triggered a
wave of panic in the areas .It is learnt the activities of these
outlawed people are spreading fast in Bagmara, Tanore and Puthia
thanas of Rajshahi district, Sadhanpur and Ballavpur areas of
Natore Sadar thana and Atrai, Rani Nagar, Porsha and Patnitola
thanas of Naogaon district.
	   The terrorists are distributing various leaflets in their
working areas secretly.The leaflets claimed that the organisational
activities of the outlaws have been geared up in Tanore with the
formation of 'guerilla units' and 'killer squads'.Informed sources
said, being weakened by factional clash in the southern region of
the country the outlaws are now trying to gear up their activities
in Rajshahi region.
	   
</TEXT>
