<BODY>
<SLUG> LANDSLIDES-FLASH-FLOOD sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BANGLADESH
</HEADLINE>
Landslides, flash flood kill six in Rangamati, THE INDEPENDENT  
   xfdws LANDSLIDES-FLASH-FLOOD sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   THE INDEPENDENT
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   Land-slides and flash flood, triggered by heavy rainfall in
Rangamati hill district killed six persons recently.
	   Crops and vegetables worth over Taka 2.5 crore were also
damaged, official sources said. Nabil Tripura (7) of Killamura
village in sadar thana of the district was buried alive when the
earthen-hut fell upon him and his family members at night when they
were asleep during the downpour on May 24. Four other members of
the family sustained injuries.
	   They were admitted to Rangamati Sadar Hospital, said Mayadhan
Chakma, Chairman of Balukhali Union Parishad. According to Bihari
Lal Chakma, Chairman of Shuvalong Union Parishad in Borkal thana of
the district , on May 23, Kazla Devi Chakma (14) and her elder
brother Indra Lal Chakma (22) of village Mitingachhari in Borkal
thana drowned when their boat capsized when they were on their way
back home.
	   Earlier, on May 21, Shariful Islam 96), Nutsey Puri Tancha-ngya
(55) and Pritimoy Tancha-ngya (45) of Kangal-chhari in Belaichhari
thana were killed by landslides. Heavy rainfall that continued for
three days damaged crops and vegetables worth over Taka 2.5 crore
in eight thanas of the district, officials of the local Agriculture
Extension Department said. Recent calamities damaged crops on 263
hectares totally and on 1,331 hectares partially , the officials
added.
	   
</TEXT>
