<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Cricket-Lara </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Lara fined 2,000 pounds for arriving late 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Brilliant West Indian batsman Brian Lara was fined
2,000 pounds (dlrs 3,260) by Warwickshire county cricket officials
Monday for arriving too late to play a crucial league match on
Sunday.
	   The Warwickshire captain missed his team's four-wicket loss to
Somerset at Taunton, blaming flight delays for his late return from
a business trip to Trinidad.
	   Lara arrived 20 minutes before the scheduled start of play but
concerned officials had already replaced him in the starting 11
because of uncertainty over his whereabouts.
	   Lara was summoned to appear before a disciplinary hearing at
Edgbaston Monday, where he was ordered to pay the fine, a small
proportion of the estimated 60,000 pounds (dlrs 98,000) he will
earn playing for Warwickshire this season.
	   Disciplinary committee spokesman Dennis Amiss said he heard a
full account from Lara about his problems and accepted there were
mitigating circumstances. Amiss also said Lara apologized to the
committee and players.
	   It is the second time this season that Lara has been delayed in
the West Indies after missing his flight back to England.
	   (jp/scw)	   
</TEXT>
