<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Proposed fare to new airport unrealistic, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws NEW-AIRPORT-UNREALISTIC sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   I AGREE with Engku Nasir's view (NST, May 22) that the proposed
fares from Kuala Lumpur to the new airport in Sepang - RM69 to RM80
by taxi, and RM31 by train - are unrealistic and frightening.
	   I remember in the late 1980s, a comfortable train ride from
Heathrow Airport to Central London was only STG1 (RM4, at the then
exchange rate) whereas taxis were charging STG15.
	   The fare must have been increased by now but it certainly would
be realistic and proportionate.
	   Based on this ratio and the 50km train ride from Central Bangkok
to Bangkok Airport for 50 sen quoted by Engku Nasir, a train fare
of RM6 to the new airport would be reasonable.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
