<HEADLINE>
HONG KONG
</HEADLINE>
Appeal to all Hong Kong emigrants, HONGKONG STANDARD  
   xfdws HONG-KONG-EMIGRANTS sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   HONGKONG STANDARD
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   The Hong Kong Standard is preparing an SAR anniversary magazine
for July 1, first anniversary of the SAR. It will include an
article on Hong Kong people who emigrated in the run-up to 1997.
	   The exodus began soon after talks on Hong Kong's future were
announced. From then until the handover more than 500,000 people
emigrated to Canada, the United States, Australia and elsewhere.
Some even went to unlikely places such as South Africa and Fiji.
	   We would very much like to hear from some of these emigrants. We
would be interested in hearing about their problems of adjustment.
We would like to know how these emigrants now feel about Hong Kong.
Do they have any regrets? Are there any organisations in Hong Kong
that try to keep in touch with these emigrants or who have
knowledge on how these emigrants are faring? How many have
returned? The first ones went that went abroad would have been away
for more than 10 years by now. Have any of these returned? Are they
sending children back? 
</TEXT>
