<HEADER>
w2773  wstm-
r i     BC-Britain-Rolls-Royce     06-01 0301
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Britain-Rolls-Royce </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Rolls-Royce enthusiasts confuse sale of carmaker with promise of bid 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Just days before Rolls-Royce Motor Cars appeared
ready to fall under German ownership, some British auto enthusiasts
muddied the picture Monday with talk of a last-minute bid.
	   Vickers PLC, the engineering group that owns Rolls-Royce,
acknowledged the deal could be delayed by the enthusiasts, although
it has received no offer from the group calling itself Crewe
Motors, named after the English town where Rolls-Royce makes its
high-priced cars.
	   The boss of Crewe Motors, London lawyer Michael Shrimpton, had
previously talked widely about making a bid, but failed to deliver.
Now, Shrimpton insists he'll try to make a credible offer, through
the investment bank Butterfield Securities, by late Wednesday.
	   Shrimpton would not identify the wealthy Rolls-Royce and Bentley
owners he says will back him, but his goal remains the same: to
keep Rolls-Royce British.
	   Vickers acknowledged a new bid, if it seemed credible, could
force a postponement in the special shareholders meeting set for
Friday. Directors have recommended that shareholders accept a bid
of 430 million pounds (dlrs 700 million) from German carmaker
Volkswagen, and they'd hoped to announce a winner Friday afternoon.
	   Volkswagen outdid an earlier bid of 340 million pounds (dlrs 554
million) from rival BMW. BMW's bid remains on the table, but the
company insists it will not raise its price.
	   Vickers spokesman Neil Hayes said that unless a bid came in from
Shrimpton's group, ``We can't tell how serious it might be.''
	   Hayes noted, however, that Shrimpton was coming along ``rather
late, and everyone's known the situation for a long time now.''
	   (db-kg)
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-Britain-Rolls-Royce; CT:i; 
(REG:EURO;)
(REG:BRIT;)
(REG:SCAN;)
(REG:MEST;)
(REG:AFRI;)
(REG:INDI;)
(REG:ENGL;)
(REG:ASIA;)
(LANG:ENGLISH;))
)
