<HEADLINE>
Greece and US joint military exercises 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   VOLOS, Greece (AP) _ About 4,500 Greek and U.S. military
personnel began training exercises Monday in the northern Aegean
Sea.
	   The NATO allies plan amphibious landings as well as joint naval
and air force maneuvers, officials said. The exercises, named for
the ancient emperor Alexander The Great, conclude Friday.
	   ``It tests us and trains us on our ability to land troops on the
ground,'' said U.S. Marine Lt. Cmdr. K.J. Braithwaite, part of the
U.S. Sixth Fleet team taking part in the exercises near Volos,
about 160 kilometers (100 miles) northwest of Athens.
	   (lo-bm)
