<HEADLINE>
EU to hold two-day Mediterraneau trade-boosting meeting in Italy 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: RETRANSMIT to fix garble in lead
<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP ) _ The European Union will hold a two-day
trade-boosting meeting with 12 Mediterranean countries in Parlermo,
Italy, this week, Foreign Secretary Robin Cook said Monday.
	   Britain, which currently hold the presidency of the EU, will
chair the meeting with foreign ministers from Algeria, Cyprus,
Egypt, Israel, Jordan, Lebanon, Malta, Morocco, Palestinian
Authority, Syria, Tunisia and Turkey.
	   The meeting, starting Wednesday, is part of the so-called
EuroMed process started at a conference in Barcelona, Spain, in
1995 to boost political, economic and cultural links between the EU
and neighbors on the southern and eastern Mediterranean rim.
	   The aim is to establish a EuroMediterranean free trade area by
2010.
