<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Learn how to outsell rivals in touch times, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws LEARN-HOW-TO-OUTSELL sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   THE downturn in the economy should not be used as an excuse for
a dip in sales performance.
	   If companies do not take a proactive stance in selling and
maintain or increasing their market shares, they would have to bear
seeing losing their customers to competitors who are more
aggressive in their strategies.
	   In view of this, Consembition Jaya Sdn Bhd is organising a
two-day workshop titled Selling in Tough Times on July 8 and 9.
	   The workshop, to be held in Petaling Jaya, is expected to help
participants to develop the right attitude towards selling, develop
a vision for successful marketing, pick up the five strategies to
build relationships with their clients, analyse their customer base
and develop ways to get repeat sales, learn the SMART formula for
sales success, study the FAB formula for sale success and learn the
11 ways to overcome objections.
	   The workshop is targeted at managers and executives across
various industries who need to increase their sales and learn to
sell in tough times.
	   For details, call the organiser at Tel: 03-3453411/1103.
	   
</TEXT>
