<HEADLINE>
Portuguese court convicts four Britons of drug smuggling 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   PORTIMAO, Portugal (AP) - A court Monday sentenced four British
men to six years in prison for smuggling hashish.
	   The five, all residents of Gibraltar, were convicted of bringing
two packages containing 54 kilograms (119 pounds) of hashish into
southern Portugal by boat.
	   The British embassy in Lisbon identified the men as Nicholas
Gill, Darrel Kerry, Alan Lopez and Karon Yusifredo.
	   The men were arrested last year in Portimao, 300 kilometers (186
miles) south of Lisbon, where they arrived by private yacht.
	   They offloaded the hashish and were burying it on a beach when
the police pounced.
	   Two other men charged, Britons John Barnham and Anthony Godding,
were acquitted.
	   (bh/cg)
