<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Need to understand transvestites, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws UNDERSTAND-TRANSVESTITES sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   COMMUNITY Aids Service Penang is saddened by the arrest of 37
transvestites in Alor Star on May 17 and their subsequent
conviction.
	   It is unfortunate that our lawmakers and enforcers are guided by
a common, but outdated, completely erroneous and unscientific view
of human physical and psychological development.
	   In our work in the community on AIDS prevention, CASP has
developed close contact with the transgender community as one of
the groups of people who are vulnerable to the transmission of HIV,
the virus that causes AIDS.
	   Syariah Court judge Sheikh Zainol Embon is quoted as saying:
``The court is very disappointed and hurt with what you did.
	   ``It looks as though you cannot accept the fact that you are men
and want to change the fact by becoming women.
	   ``Acts of men dressing or acting like women and vice versa are
loathed by religion and deserve severe punishment.'' (NST, May 24).
	   Modern scientific understanding is that there is a full
gradation between male and female and not a clear dividing line, no
black and white, but only shades of gray.
	   It is our incapability to accept them as they are that is the
problem.
	   By not accepting the transgendered as created by God, we push
them into the margins of society where using drugs and finding sex
are the only way to make a living.
	   It is unfortunate that religion is so often used to create
outcasts in society rather than bring universal love and acceptance
to all of God's creation.
	   It is time for Malaysians to discuss more openly our prejudices
towards the transgendered and other sexual minorities and strive
towards creating a really caring society.
	   We need to have better scientific and psychosocial knowledge in
this area so we can help and counsel this group more effectively
and develop a truly caring society.
	   
</TEXT>
