<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
PeopleSoft to set up local office, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws TO-SET-UP-LOCAL-OFFICE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   ENTERPRISE resource planning solutions vendor PeopleSoft Inc is
setting up a direct presence in Malaysia with the opening of an
office in Kuala Lumpur within the next three to six months.
	   The local office will kick off operations by providing customer
support services to the company's distributors and partners here,
said PeopleSoft Asia Pte Ltd's managing director Asean Robert
Squires.
	   According to Squires, PeopleSoft will also garner feedback from
these partners in terms of additional requirements which are later
channelled through the company's local outfit.
	   ``The office will progressively grow to assist our partners in
the execution of business,'' he told Computimes during a Press
briefing in Subang Jaya last Thursday.
	   Squires said PeopleSoft is continuing to invest in Asean despite
the current economic downturn.
	   ``The company is re-focusing on its core competencies and
restructuring the business to be ready for the upturn of the
economy when the time comes.''
	   He added that the time was right for the company to continue
investing in the region.
	   He said the company is confident that this is an effective and
strategic decision for PeopleSoft and its distributors and
partners.
	   Commenting on the company's local distribution channel, Squires
said PeopleSoft would maintain the existing structure, with no
plans to either reduce or expand the network.
	   The company's business this year, he said, is projected to grow
but he declined to disclose any figures.
	   ``It will be a slower one as compared to the company's growth in
the last year,'' he said.
	   At the same event, Squires also announced the official opening
of a new office site in Singapore which serves as the company's
business hub for Asean and the launch of PeopleSoft Version 7.5
enterprise application suite.
	   The new suite, which offers the financials, distribution and
manufacturing modules, will be available in the region next month
while the human resources and payroll systems will be in the market
in the fourth quarter of this year.
	   The new release leverages on technology features of PeopleSoft
7, for instance, Web client, a high performance three-tier
processing option and online analytical processing (OLAP)
integration providing additional technology enhancements in its Web
client, application server, workflow, and support for IBM AS/400
computing platform.
	   Key features in PeopleSoft's Version 7.5 include global
application and functionality such as global supply chain
management optimism capability, support for European and Monetary
Union and international accounting practices, a European Payroll
application, and enhancements to support regional and
multinationals.
	   Other features include applications such as the Treasury
application suite and a new Expenses application; Stock
Administration and Quality, Performance Management application
suite, a new Demand Planning application, and an enhanced Budgets
and Human Resources application.
	   
</TEXT>
