<BODY>
<SLUG> ERGONOMICALLY-CORRECT sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Ergonomically correct, MALAYSIAN BUSINESS  
   xfdws ERGONOMICALLY-CORRECT sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 16, 1998
   MALAYSIAN BUSINESS
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   ATTENTION to ergonomics makes Recaro seats different from other
run-of-the-mill car seats. Jurgen Fritz, Recaro South East Asia Sdn
Bhd managing director, says Recaro's design ensures a motorist sits
properly with an emphasis on relieving the stress imposed on the
spine and muslces. `Every Recaro seat offers correct ergonomics as
well as comfort,' he says.
	   Sitting ergonomically correctly requires the upholstery to be
tailored to support the spine. Ergonomics, in fact, is the first
cornerstone in the Recaro engineering design. The seat also needs
cushioning properties to ease stress on the thighs. Seat height and
tilt should be variable, giving the occupant complete control. Side
bolsters on the seat cushion, lumbar support and backrest should be
optimally-shaped for better support.
	   Fritz says the basis of Recaro's unique construction principle
is known as the closed back shell. `This provides the base for the
ergonomically- shaped upholster. This is shaped in such a way that
your weight is evenly distributed and your muscles remain relaxed,'
he says.
	   Its second cornerstone is safety. Recaro seats have a higher
than normal backrest which provides optimum support for the entire
back. Its fully- upholstered headrest is height and tilt
adjustable, providing optimal damping of a head impact. Its back
shell is entirely enclosed for improved protection from sliding
luggage. The seat cushion is shaped with a strong cross member in
the frame to prevent submarining in the event of a front collision,
without which a person slides under the seat belt.
	   Fritz says comfort is Recaro's third engineering cornerstone.
`The design ensures reduced vibration, increased cushioning and
optimum support,' he says. Throughout the world, Recaro seats are
coveted for its upmarket appeal. `This is our fourth cornerstone -
styling,' says Fritz.
	   He says a good design always goes hand in hand with
functionality. He says the Recaro design combines stylish elegance
which blends well with the individual car's interior. `Our seats
are predominantly made painstakingly by hand. This allows all
aspects of the seat design to be meticulously prepared so that the
completed seat fits together perfectly,' says Fritz.
	   
</TEXT>
