<TEXT>
	   DIAMOND Multimedia, a supplier of graphics and sound
accelerators and the Supra series of modems, has appointed Eileen
Goh as channel marketing manager, Asia-Pacific.
	   Goh, who holds a Bachelor of Arts in English Language and
Psychology from the National University of Singapore, is based at
the company's headquarters in Singapore. Her responsibilities
include support of channel partner and business alliance
programmes.
	   Diamond Multimedia provides advanced solutions for home,
business and professional desktop computer users, enabling them to
create, access and experience compelling new media content from
their desktops and through the Internet. Diamond accelerates
multimedia from the internet to the hard drive with products that
include the Stealth and Viper series of media accelerators, the
Monster series of entertainment 3D and sound accelerators, the Fire
series of professional 3D and SCSI accelerators, and the Supra
series of modems.
	   The company also markets DVD and video phone kits. Diamond's
common stock is traded on the Nesdaq Stock Market under the symbol
DIMD, and its web site address is www.diamondmm.com 
