<SLUG> BC-Air France-Strike, 4th Ld </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Passengers stranded as Air France strike begins lasts the 15 days; color; UPDATES with quotes from Marseille airport 
</HEADLINE>
EDS: CLARIFIES 4th graf to show walkout biggest in 27 years IF it
AP Photos PAR101-104
By CHRISTOPHER BURNS
Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Thousands of frustrated passengers were stranded at
airports across the country Monday, after Air France pilots began a
strike that threatened to disrupt travel plans during the World
Cup.
	   Monitors at Paris' main airports offered a bleak sight for
passengers: departure screens flashing ``annule'' and ``canceled''
in bright red letters next to nearly all Air France flights nine
days before the soccer championship begins.
	   The jets of the official airline for the World Cup, many
decorated with players representing the 32 teams, sat idle at
terminals. Their 3,200 pilots sought to block wage cuts aimed at
keeping the newly profitable state-owned airline out of the red.
	   The walkout would be Air France's biggest in 27 years if it
lasts the 15 days striking pilots have threatened, and was a
serious embarrassment to the leftist government of Prime Minister
Lionel Jospin.
	   Frustrated passengers lined up at Air France ticket counters at
Charles de Gaulle Airport in Paris, hoping to switch their tickets
to other carriers.
	   Nicolas Minvelle, hoping to leave on vacation to Senegal, said
it wasn't fair the pilots were striking ahead of the World Cup,
being played in 10 cities across France.
	   ``They use an international event to bother everyone, it's too
bad. That's not the image of France, it should be avoided. You can
say they are not civic-minded,'' he said.
	   Yelena Panteley, a Russian student from California, was on her
way to see her mother in Saint Petersburg, hoping to catch an
alternate flight. ``There is hope, but nothing's sure.''
	   However, some airports, like those in Lyon and Marseille, were
almost deserted. Passengers warned in advance of the strike stayed
away.
	   Under normal circumstances, 9th graf pvs (eg)
