<TEXT>
	   FILLING up at the forecourt cannot be easier. Shell Malaysia has
launched Shell Easy Pay where all one needs to do is to drive up,
fill up and just go! This `no cash, no card' concept works via an
easily-acquired transponder tag encoded with a Shell customer's
credit card and Bonuslink accounts. The exact fuel purchase will
automatically be charged to the customer's credit card and the
Bonuslink record updated. For a limited period, the tags will be
issued free. Malaysia is the first country in Asia and the third
worldwide (after the United States and Canada) where this advanced
pump payment system is being implemented. It is currently available
at five Shell stations in Subang Jaya.
	   
