<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Accessing financial services through 7-Eleven, MALAYSIAN BUSINESS  
   xfdws ACCESSING-FINANCIAL sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 31, 1998
   MALAYSIAN BUSINESS
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   THE 7-Eleven stores are the first convenience stores to provide
full-service automated financial services to consumers in Austin,
Texas (United States).
	   The Southland Corporation (which operates, franchises and
licenses approximately 17,200 7-Eleven stores worldwide) and NCR
Corporation recently unveiled a state-of-the-arts financial service
centre which will use NCR's personaS Self-Service solutions
technology to provide various services like cheque cashing, bill
payments, money transfers, money orders and phone card purchases.
Sophisticated call centre technology provides remote operator
assistance to help manage advanced financial transactions and
answer consumer questions.
	   `Like consumers around the globe, 7-Eleven customers are
demanding greater access to a wide variety of services,' said Clark
Matthews, president and CEO of The Southland Corporation. NCR's
products, Matthews believes, will help his company deliver these
services conveniently and consistently.
	   Working with Southland, Western Union and Affiliated Computer
Services (ACS), NCR designed, developed and tested the complete
kiosk solution, including applications, integrated terminal
hardware devices and networking connections to the on-line systems
at ACS. NCR personaS 40 mini ATM and Kiosk terminals support an
array of technology such as document scanning, cash acceptance,
specialised printers for money orders and phone cards, check image
processing and coin dispensing.
	   
</TEXT>
