<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-06 11:32:00 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
w2929  wstm-
r w     GRANITE'S-PRICE-LIKELYsk     06-01 0895
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> GRANITE'S-PRICE-LIKELY sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Granite's price likely to trend upwards, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws GRANITE'S-PRICE-LIKELY sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   CONTINUING weakness on the regional equities and currency
markets caused price trends on the local bourse to slip further on
lack of fresh leads on the local front.
	   Comments by economists and analysts that the country's economic
growth was worse than forecast earlier depressed share prices even
further.
	   Last week, the KLSE Composite Index fell 38.99 points, or 6.76
per cent, when compared to the previous week's close of 577.23
level. The KLSE All Share EMAS Index (KLSE EMAS) closed 8.41
points, or 5.80 per cent, lower to 136.51 level. Thus, the KLSE
EMAS had out-performed the KLSE CI by 96 basis points. The
out-performance posted by the KLSE EMAS was due primarily to many
second and third liners' retracement to the 1990/1991 levels.
	   Many of these second and third liners had since breached the
RM1.00 level while some had even dropped below the 50 sen support
level. Granite Industries Bhd (Granite) is one such counter that
fell from grace.
	   Granite was one of the stock market darlings during the 1993
superbull run. Its price trend rose from its intra-year low of
RM1.08 on Jan 5, 1993 to its all-time high of RM16.60 on Dec 12,
1993, posting a whopping gain of RM15.52, or 1,437.04 per cent,
over a 12-month period. Since then, its price trend had collapsed
down to its recent low of 44.5 sen level on May 14, 1998. The
company was formed on Dec 31, 1968 as a joint venture between Chee
Tat Realty Private Ltd, a company incorporated in Singapore and
Castle  Cooke Inc of Hawaii, USA.
	   Since then, the major shareholdings had changed hands several
times.
	   After several changes, Tan Sri Datuk Ting Pek Khiing emerged as
the single largest shareholder with direct and indirect interest of
26.13 and 9.91 per cent respectively on May 2, 1996.
	   Granite is principally an investment holding company with
subsidiaries involved in timber moulding and related activities,
operation of hotels, general trading, property development, supply
of machines and provision of services in the leisure and
entertainment industry.
	   On May 6, 1997, the company had entered into subscription
agreements to acquire 99.99 per cent stakes in Langkasuka Resorts
Sdn Bhd, Aquabeat Langkawi Sdn Bhd and Langkawi Exhibition Hall Sdn
Bhd for a total consideration of RM176.6 million. A proposed
5-for-3 rights issue was supposed to raise the necessary funding
but the proposed acquisition was called off in October 1997.
	   Chartwise, Granite's price trend peaked at RM16.60 level on Dec
22, 1993. Since then, its price trend continued to drift lower and
lower when the corporate activities shifted to timber and operation
of hotels.
	   Its price trend hit its recent retracement low of 44.5 sen on
May 14, 1998, giving a total retracement loss of RM16.155, or 97.32
per cent, from its all-time historical high of RM16.60 level.
	   Here are the readings of some of its technical indicators:-
Moving Averages: Its price trend continued to stay below all its
10-, 20-, 30-, 50-, 100- and 200-day moving averages.
	   Momentum Index: Its short-term momentum index encountered
resistance at its neutral reference line.
	   On Balance Volume: Its short-term OBV trend continued to stay
below its 10-day exponential moving averages.
	   Relative Strength Index: Its 14-RSI rebounded on the strength of
its positive divergence to that of the price trend.
	   OUTLOOK: Granite's diversification into the timber and
hospitality industry yielded steady return to profitability. Its
further diversification into the hospitality industry was hampered
by the current economic and financial turmoil.
	   From its substantial shareholders' filings of Form 29B on May
20, 1998, it was noted that See Hoy Chan Properties Sdn Bhd and
associates had been steadily building up their holdings in Granite
to 17.532 million shares.
	   Is it purely for investment purposes?
	   Technically, Granite's price trend has since retraced to its new
low since 1989. Certainly, its current levels have minimal downside
risks as its all-time historical low was at 35 sen level.
Currently, its price trend remains around its current level (See
Granite's weekly bar chart - E1-E2).
	   From its daily bar chart, Granite's price trend is likely to
move out of its short-term downtrend (F3-F4) on its sideway course.
Once it moves out of its short-term downtrend, Granite's price
trend is likely to initiate a technical rebound to re-challenge its
next overhead resistance (F1-F2) over its intermediate-term
perspectives.
	   
</TEXT>
