<TEXT>
	   SPARE a thought for our disabled brethren and emulate the
example of AMIM Holdings Sdn Bhd, the assembler and distributor of
Ford vehicles in Malaysia. It has introduced the Ford Disabled
Package to help people with special needs to become more
independent. AMIM Holdings general manager Richard Canny says the
package is specifically designed for the Laser Lynx and is fitted
free of charge to any certified disabled buyer with a valid
Malaysian driving licence. A group of disabled drivers from the
Damai Disabled Training Centre in Petaling Jaya was given the
opportunity to test drive a Ford Lynx fitted with the package
recently. 'Ford believes the disabled should be assisted to be as
mobile and independent as everybody else - whether to explore this
beautiful country, drive themselves to town to do some shopping or
simply visit friends and family without having to arrange for
transportation assistance,' says Canny.
	   
