<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1044 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Conditions will remain similar to yesterday. The heating of the
day and the afternoon sea breeze will produce some showers and an
isolated thunderstorm or two, mainly over the western interior and
northwest.
	   High pressure anchored over the north central Atlantic will
drift to the east by tomorrow, turning winds across our local
islands more southeast and increasing the flow of moist air over
Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands. This will produce warmer
than normal temperatures over the northern sections of Puerto Rico.
	   Small craft operators should use caution in the offshore waters
of the Atlantic and Caribbean due to fresh east to southeast winds.
Near shore waters will see some chop by afternoon due to an
increasing sea breeze.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variably cloudy in the
afternoon with a 30 percent chance of showers. Isolated afternoon
thunderstorms, mainly in the west. High 85 to 90. Wind east at 10
to 15 mph, except northeast along the coast in the afternoon.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers,
mainly in the east. Low 75 to 80. Wind becoming southeast around 5
mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy in the morning. Increasing cloudiness
in the afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers. Isolated
thunderstorms. High near 90. Wind southeast at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers,
mainly in the morning. High 85 to 90. Wind east at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of a thunderstorm. Low 70 to 80. Wind becoming
southeast at less than 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High around 85. Wind southeast 10
to 15 mph.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers. High
85 to 90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph, except southeast along the coast.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers,
mainly in the east. Slight chance of a thunderstorm in the east.
Low 65 to 75. Wind east near 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variably cloudy in the
afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers. Isolated
thunderstorms, mainly in the west. High 85 to 90. Wind becoming
southeast at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly sunny in the morning. Variably cloudy afternoon
with a 40 percent chance of showers. Isolated thunderstorms. High
85 to 90. Wind east 10 to 20 mph, except for an afternoon sea
breeze less than 10 mph along the coast.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a less than 20 percent chance of
showers. Low 70 to 75. Wind light from the southeast.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variably cloudy
afternoon with a 50 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms.
High 80 to 90. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph, except for an afternoon
sea breeze less than 10 mph along the coast in the afternoon.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variably cloudy in the
afternoon with a 40 percent chance of showers or thunderstorms.
High from 75 to 80 in the mountains to 85 to 90 in lower
elevations. Wind east at 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers,
mainly during the evening in the west and late in the day in the
east. Low from around 65 mountains to near 75 in lower elevations.
Wind becoming southeast at less than 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy in the morning. Variably cloudy in the
afternoon with a 50 percent chance of showers or thunderstorms.
High from 75 to 80 in the mountains to 85 to 90 in lower
elevations. Wind southeast at 10 to 15 mph.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers. High
85 to 90. Wind southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 80. Wind east 5 to 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High 85 to 90. Wind becoming
southeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft should exercise caution in offshore waters.
	   Today... Wind east to southeast 10 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft.
Widely scattered showers.
	   Tonight... Wind becoming southeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to 4 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind southeast at 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to 4 ft. Widely
scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft should exercise caution in offshore waters.
	   Today... Wind east to southeast at 10 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 5 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind becoming southeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind southeast at 10 to 15 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft. Widely
scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 kt, except locally
variable 10 kt or less along the coast. Seas 2 to 3 ft. Widely
scattered showers.
	   Tonight... Wind east to southeast at 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to 3
ft. Isolated showers.
	   Tuesday... Wind southeast 10 to 15 kt, except locally variable
10 kt or less along the coast. Seas 1 to 3 ft. Widely scattered
showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Tuesday night through Friday... Winds east to southeast 20 kt or
less. Seas 6 ft or less.
</TEXT>
