<SLUG> BC-Obit-Brojan Das </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Six time conqueror of English Channel dies 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) _ Brojan Das, a Bangladesh national who
swam across the English Channel six times, died in the Indian city
of Calcutta on Monday at the age of 71, his family said.
	   Das was the first Asian to cross the channel, in 1958 and set a
speed record in 1961. He was hospitalized in Calcutta with a heart
ailment, his family members said, asking not to be identified by
name.
	   He is survived by his wife, a son and a daughter.
	     (hs/kg)
</TEXT>
