<SLUG> BC-Russia-Murders </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Man gets death penalty for 7 killings, including friend planning to emigrate 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A former tax police officer was sentenced to death
Monday for killing seven people, including his girlfriend who
planned to emigrate to Israel, a news agency reported.
	   Valery Kulakov, 25, killed two families in the Ural Mountains
city of Yekaterinburg in October 1996 by slitting their throats,
Interfax said.
	   Police found five bodies, including that of his girlfriend and
another woman who planned to emigrate, in one apartment. Two other
victims, thought to have been witnesses, were found in another
building.
	   Kulakov's lawyer said he would appeal the death sentence.
	   (ls) 	   
</TEXT>
