<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-World Cup-Romania,0265 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Romania sets sights on semi-finals 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   SAFTICA, Romania (AP) _ Romania's soccer team hopes to make it
into the semi-finals of this summer's World Cup in France, topping
its performance of four years ago, when it fell in the
quarterfinals.
	   ``We might qualify for semifinals if we play well,'' said
Gheorghe Popescu, a key part of Romania's defense, who plays for
Turkey's champion Galatasaray.
	   His teammate with Galatasaray, Gheorghe Hagi, known as ``the
Maradona of the Carpathians,'' said Romania's most difficult game
would be its first one, June 15 against Colombia.
	   Although Romania beat Colombia in 1994 play, the first match is
often the toughest psychologically.
	   Dan Petrescu, a player for England's Chelsea, said Romania's
tournament strategy will depend on whether the team beats Colombia.
	   Romania plays in Group G, along with Colombia, England and
Tunisia. Romania and England are considered the front-runners.
	   Romania scored nine victories and one draw qualifying for the
World Cup.
	   The team achieved its best showing in the 1994 World Cup,
beating Colombia and the United States in the first round, and even
Argentina in a wild second-round match. Romania later fell to
Sweden in the quarterfinals.
	   The national team currently trains at their base of Saftica, 20
kilometers (12 miles) north of Bucharest.
	   Coach Anghel Iordanescu is expected to announce the line-up for
the World Cup soon. Romania will have two warm-up games, with
Paraguay and Moldova, before leaving June 8 for France. 	   
</TEXT>
