<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Opportunity to sample goods before buying them, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws OPPORTUNITY-TO-SAMPLE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   CRABTREE  Evelyn (Malaysia) Sdn Bhd, a wholly-owned subsidiary
of Kuala Lumpur Kepong Bhd, opened its flagship store at the Suria
Kuala Lumpur City Centre on Friday.
	   The store, which is the biggest in the Asia-Pacific region,
sells toiletries and fine food.
	   Crabtree  Evelyn also has another outlet at the Starhill Centre
which was opened last December.
	   Asia-Pacific sales and marketing manager Frederic Puech, who was
present at the opening, said that there were 62 outlets in the
Asia-Pacific region and they are considering opening another in
Penang.
	   ``Penang is a possibility but for the moment we will concentrate
on promoting our flagship store at the KLCC,'' said Puech.
	   The promotion campaign is by way of encouraging customers to
experience the products themselves.
	   ``In the case of our soaps, customers can actually wash their
hands with the various kinds of soap. For that purpose we have a
wash basin available. We want our customers to browse around the
outlet and sample the products.
	   ``During the months of May and June visitors to the store will
be treated to food tasting and aromatherapy hand massage. Shoppers
can also take advantage of special gifts with purchases.
	   ``Our prices are very competitive and our products are of very
high quality,'' said Puech.
	   He did not want to reveal the total investment in Malaysia.
	   On the products sold in the outlet, Puech said all of them are
manufactured overseas.
	   ``The soaps are made in Switzerland while the perfumes are from
France.
	   Toiletries are from Wales while some food products are from
England.''
	   KLK bought over Crabtree  Evelyn in July 1996.
	   
</TEXT>
