<HEADLINE>
Six-time conqueror of English Channel dies 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) _ Brojan Das, a Bangladesh national who
swam across the English Channel six times, died Monday in the
Indian city of Calcutta, his family said. He was 71.
	   He was hospitalized in Calcutta with a heart ailment, his family
members said, asking not to be identified by name.
	   Das was the first Asian to cross the channel in 1958 and set a
speed record in 1961.
	   He is survived by his wife, a son and a daughter.
