<TEXT>
	   THE Electronic Products Division (EPD) of Canon Marketing (M)
Sdn Bhd recently held its 1998 National Sales and Support Seminar
at the head office in Petaling Jaya. About 60 participants attended
the event, including EPD staff from the Peninsular Malaysia
branches.
	   The purpose of the seminar was to motivate and enhance staff
morale, as well as to enable them to exchange information and gain
knowledge about new products and market situation.
	   The event was officially opened by Canon Malaysia's managing
director Jack Lim, whose opening speech got participants in the
right mood. Among the special guests at the opening ceremony were
Canon Singapore Pte Ltd's general manager Kazuto Ogawa, marketing
manager Clara Lim, and marketing executive Fennie Ong. The seminar
consisted of a product workshop, motivational talk, corporate games
and also EPD's business outlook in general.
	   EPD's general manager Liew Sip Chon stressed that teamwork,
commitment, keen desire to work and self-confidence were key
success factors to the company's achievements.
	   
