<BODY>
<SLUG> LEARNING-BASICS sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Learning basics with Sesame Street Toddlers Deluxe, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws LEARNING-BASICS sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   THE highly-acclaimed television programme Sesame Street has now
entered the realm of interactive technology. The Sesame Street
Toddlers Deluxe comes bundled with three compact disks (CDs) and no
prizes for guessing what they do. Those of you who grew up watching
the Street programme will surely remember the days when you learnt
to recite your ABCs, count your 123s and dance to the tune of
Do-Re-Me together with the furry, memorable, cuddly creations from
the late Jim Henson's workshop.
	   But what makes this software package delightful is that it
continues the Street's legacy of portraying the same zestful and
eccentric ensemble of muppets.
	   And doing what it does best, which is educating and entertaining
young viewers, this package offers pre-school children the choice
of a variety of learning activities ranging from recognising
letters and numbers to rhyming and art work.
	   Watch your kids get mesmerised by the eye-catching interface as
Elmo (my personal favourite) guides them to learning the rudiments
of knowledge.
	   Along the way, introduce them to a ``star-studded'' cast of
muppets like the nasal-voiced Grover and the ever-deliciously
wicked Street inhabitant known as Oscar the Grouch, who, for some
reason, has this inane attachment to his dumpster and develops
insecurities whenever having to leave it.
	   Then, there's the mismatched pair, Ernie and Bert, the misfit
Cookie Monster and of course, the one-and-only Big Bird.
	   Young viewers may not know this but parents who ardently follow
the Street TV show, might recognise some similarities with the way
the whole teaching processes here are being presented. While
reviewing this software, I felt like I was watching the TV series
all over again.
	   And be prepared for some pretty witty scripts. Children (and
parents alike) will be tickled pink to hear the usual banter,
spiced with a dash of humour of course between Ernie and Bert as
you pay these guys a visit.
	   Or have your child rummage through Snuffleupagus' and Big Bird's
homes to uncover the essential items that one is asked to look for.
And if you simply want to take a break, how about listening to some
songs?
	   Interested? Want to know more?
	   Well, Disk One unveils a series of activities covering areas
like art and colouring using stickers and rubber stamps. Or how
about creating slide shows from selected pictures? Here, children
are exposed to verbal instructions and by following them, they can
gradually pick up the basics of computer skills. After the
``getting-to-know-your-PC'' exercise, Disk Two then introduces
toddlers to the alphabet, phonics and rhyming with the aim to
helping children slowly develop their vocabulary skills.
	   And surprise! surprise! There are even classic videos excerpts
and songs from the TV show to add fun and variety.
	   Feel like moving on? Well, there's Disk Three which progresses
to the more difficult part of the learning process. There are
lessons on numbers and games to play, in addition to songs to sing
along to and storytelling.
	   Help Count von Count find his bats in his castle and learn all
about addition and subtraction.
	   And parents, are you looking for comprehensive educational CDs
that are worth your time and money?
	   Why not give Sesame Street Toddlers Deluxe a try. And who knows,
someday when that familiar Street tune is played, your child will
sit back and say, ``Hey, that really brings back memories''.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
(PROFILE
(WS SL:LEARNING-BASICS sked; CT:w; 
(REG:ENGL;)
