<SLUG> THE-MILLION-MARK sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
The million mark, MALAYSIAN BUSINESS  
   xfdws THE-MILLION-MARK sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 16, 1998
   MALAYSIAN BUSINESS
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   THE softening demand for cars in the face of the current
economic downturn has been a humbling experience for Edaran
Otomobil Nasional Bhd (EON), the distributor of the national car.
In the past, buyers had to grit their teeth when faced with the
`non-option' of having to purchase Proton cars complete with
`optional accessories'. Now they can buy the `no-frills' Proton
Iswara 1.3 litre Aeroback which, with excise duty, sales tax and
air-conditioner but minus all the other extras, is some RM9,000
cheaper! This has attracted so many customers that EON is expecting
to celebrate a milestone this month - its millionth sale. New
customers can also enjoy reduced interest rates on car loans, from
10 per cent to 9.5 per cent.
	   Roll on, customer number 1,000,000.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 MALAYSIAN BUSINESS all rights reserved as
distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
