<BODY>
<SLUG> HUNCHBACK-OF-NOTRE-DAME sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Hunchback of Notre Dame adventure, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws HUNCHBACK-OF-NOTRE-DAME sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   GLORIOUS church bells and beautiful orchestra music welcome
everyone to another exciting Disney adventure! Those are the bells
of Notre Dame and so begins a story behind those chimes - Disney's
Animated StoryBook: The Hunchback of Notre Dame.
	   The story begins with Quasimodo, a meek and mild hunchback.
Frollo, a cruel and wicked man, raised him. He lives in the Notre
Dame cathedral and, at Frollo's instructions, does not wander
outside the cathedral.
	   Everyday he watches life passing below in the streets,
especially during the gala and whimsical Festival of Fools.
	   The Festival of Fools is an annual event that parades the
silliest performances for the year as the crowd looks for a person
who has the ugliest face to be crowned as king of the festival.
	   Quasimodo is sad as he cannot attend the festival but his
gargoyle friends Hugo, Victor and Laverne have other plans.
	   With encouragement from these friends, Quasimodo climbs down the
cathedral and mingles with the people at the Festival of Fools.
Here, he meets two new friends in Esmeralda, a gypsy woman and
Phoebus, an army captain, and is crowned the king of the festival
by the crowd.
	   Frightened and scared by the fruits thrown by the crowd, he
flees back to Notre Dame followed unknowingly by Esmeralda. Phoebus
follows her into Notre Dame to help her to escape the clutches of
Frollo but Frollo himself soon discovers this.
	   However, Frollo cannot capture her as she has sought sanctuary
in the cathedral. In the dark of the night, Quasimodo helps
Esmeralda escape by climbing down the cathedral. Later, Quasimodo
overhears that Frollo and his soldiers are going to raid the secret
Court of Miracles and capture all the gypsies hiding there. Off go
Quasimodo and Phoebus in their quest to find the secret Court and
warn of the dangers that lie ahead.
	   To play the game, merely click on the hero to go directly to the
story.
	   Otherwise, click on Clopin the puppet to learn to play together.
Clopin will then take you to a Choice Screen with a range of
options.
	   To read and play with the story, click on the picture of Hugo
and Victor together. Your kids could also sit back and relax as the
story is read to them by clicking the picture of Victor reading a
storybook.
	   To go straight to your favourite part of the story, click on the
picture of Laverne and the pigeons. Or else, click on the picture
of Hugo juggling to play the fun-filled games. Your kids can use
the tomato cursor to move around the screen and to click on an
object.
	   Two things I like the most about this animated storybook are the
exciting games and musical scores. Firstly, your kids will get the
chance to play the Bells Game. They will learn to cheer up
Quasimodo by composing some songs and dancing some numbers for him.
Click on any of the eight coloured bells in the Bell Tower to
create a sequence of musical sounds.
	   As each sound is played, the gargoyle at the centre of the stage
will do the twist, roll, raise his hands up and down and sideways
and swing his hips. Clicking on the scroll above the stage saves
the song sheets. You can also select any gargoyle that you want to
perform on stage by clicking on that particular gargoyle and
dragging him to the centre of the stage.
	   There is also a game called Tightrope walker.
	   Here your kids need to help Jacques the Magnificent to walk
safely across the tightrope by balancing the number of chickens on
both sides of the pole he carries. Help is also vital to guide Hugo
to stop the soldiers from getting to the top of the cathedral by
dropping boxes on the soldiers as they climb up the ladders.
	   Sing-alongs can be heard in the Festival of Fools. Your kids
will be invited to sing along with Clopin and the band by following
the bouncing chickens.
	   There are three different songs provided at the banner located
at the right side of the screen. Your kids will enjoy many more
games that are included here. It's enough to keep any young one
engrossed for hours.
	   MINIMUM SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS:
	   Intel 80486 processor, 66MHz Microsoft Windows 95, Windows
version 3.1x or later 8MB RAM 30MB free disk space
Microsoft-compatible mouse Standard AT-101 keyboard 256-colour
VESA, PCI or other local bus video Windows compatible 8-bit or
16-bit sound card 2X CD-ROM drive (or better) - minimum 300KB
transfer rate
	   
</TEXT>
