<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
New routers offer fast access over analogue lines, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws NEW-ROUTERS-OFFER sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   3Com Corp has announced the availability of its OfficeConnect
Remote Dual Analogue router which is designed to enable access to
information at the fastest speeds possible over analogue lines.
	   According to 3Com's product line manager for entry-level systems
PDD Andrew Moloney, the product is able to offer a near-integrated
services digital network (ISDN) speed of 112 kilobits per second,
which is equivalent to the power of two 56Kbps modems.
	   He claimed the router also offers functionality over standard
analogue lines but without the costs that are normally associated
with maintaining a digital service.
	   ``This product is ideal for small and mid-sized businesses
because these outfits might not have the technical expertise to
install complex products but need the advanced technology to keep
them competitive in the current market,'' he added.
	   Moloney said the new router is simple to install as users need
only to connect their existing unit to their computer and existing
phone lines.
	   ``Once done, the hypertext markup language (HTML) Web-based tool
takes the users through the configuration process. The system is
usually up and running in under 30 minutes.''
	   With the new router, small organisations now have a high
performance networking solution with competitive benefits that are
typically found in large companies, according to Moloney.
	   ``Organisations are now capable of implementing applications
like electronic-mail (e-mail) while extending the local area
network (LAN) to remote users,'' he said, adding that the router
utilises already existing analogue phone lines to offer the
benefits of high-speed information access.
	   Another member of the OfficeConnect family is the Dual Speed Hub
8 which provides eight twisted-pair connections. With a built-in
switch and Class II Fast Ethernet repeater, the product is designed
specifically to cascade to other hubs and permit connection of up
to four hubs in a series, Moloney said.
	   Meanwhile, the OfficeConnect Switch 400 provides the flexibility
in small-office switching. According to Moloney, users will be able
to migrate effortlessly between 10 megabits per second and 100Mbps
with the performance benefits of switching.
	   Certified for domestic environments, the switch is designed to
provide maximum throughput of 400Mbps and a direct connection to a
server or end station or even to another hub or switch, he added.
	   Now available in the market, the router is priced at US$745
(RM2,830).
	   The hub costs US$755 while the switch is priced at US$755.
	   
</TEXT>
