<HEADLINE>
Israeli army jeep hits suspected Palestinian infiltrators 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ An Israeli army jeep collided Monday with a car
carrying six Palestinians who sneaked into Israel from the Gaza
Strip, the army said.
	   The Palestinians tried to escape in a waiting car with an
Israeli license plate, the army said.
	   When an Israeli army jeep tried to block the car, the two
vehicles collided, the army said. Two soldiers and two of the
Palestinians were slightly injured. The other four were arrested.
	   In a separate incident, the Israeli army set up checkpoints
Monday around the Palestinian village of El Khader in the West Bank
after shots were fired toward two Israeli vehicles on a highway
that passes the village.
