<HEADLINE>
At Entertainment drops Poland's Canal Plus in cable TV enterprise 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   WARSAW, Poland (AP) _ The U.S.-based At Entertainment Inc. said
Monday it had dropped plans to develop a digital pay-TV service in
Poland with Canal Plus, and that it would develop one alone.
	   The two companies had signed a letter of intent for the joint
venture but could not agree on details before a May 31 deadline,
said Przemyslaw Szmyt, a deputy president of At Entertainment.
	   Szmyt declined to discuss details of the talks between the two
companies. Canal Plus Poland, a subsidiary of Europe's largest
cable TV company Canal Plus, declined to comment.
	   At Entertainment plans to start its own digital TV service in
September, Szmyt said.
	   The Hartford, Connecticut-based company already runs the largest
cable television network in Poland reaching 800,000 homes. It is to
launch an additional cable TV network this week, Szmyt said.
	   (ms-im)
</TEXT>
