<SLUG> AWARD-TO-RECOGNISE sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Awards to recognise excellence in IT, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws AWARD-TO-RECOGNISE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   FOR the past nine years, the Association of the Computer
Industry Malaysia (Pikom) and Computimes have worked together to
recognise excellence in information technology through the annual
IT Awards.
	   The practice of identifying outstanding organisations, products
and content in IT for their contributions continues with the 1998
Pikom-Computimes IT Awards. As in the past years, the aim is to
give recognition to organisations making effective use of IT, and
hardware, software and content developers who excel in their
fields.
	   The awards have produced an impressive list of winners, with
locally-developed offerings that not only made an impact locally
but were also able to compete internationally.
	   With the current emphasis on Made-in-Malaysia products,
competition in the various categories of the IT Awards is expected
to be more intense, and even more interesting.
	   To ensure that the entries received meet the requirements given,
a technical evaluation committee has been set up.
	   The committee, headed by Stacks Technology Sdn Bhd's managing
director Nah Soo Hoe, comprises representatives from the Government
and the private sector.
	   At a recent meeting, the organising committee decided that the
categories for the IT Awards should remain at six.
	   However, based on the feedback received, the IT Product of the
Year (Systems) category has been scrapped as it was difficult to
evaluate and attracted the least number of entries each year.
	   Instead, the software category was expanded to cover IT Product
of the Year (Software: Application) and IT Product of the Year
(Software: Internet-based Application), taking into account current
trends in the industry.
	   The six categories in this year's IT Awards are: IT Organisation
of the Year - for a local organisation or Government body which has
been successful in using IT effectively; IT Product of the Year
(Hardware) -for commercially available product with at least 30 per
cent local content or design; IT Product of the Year (Software:
Application) - for commercially available software application of
local design; IT Product of the Year (Software: Internet-based
Application) - for commercially available Internet-based
application of local design; Internet Web site of the Year - for
locally-developed Web site which has been successful in helping an
organisation or community; and Multimedia CD-Title of the Year -
for locally-developed multimedia compact disk title which has made
the most impact.
	   Pikom's chairman Shaifubahrim Saleh said the organisers are
expecting more entries this year, and the process to make
nominations has been simplified.
	   Nominations for the awards are now open. To nominate, either
visit the Pikom Web site at www. pikom.org.my or call Fahiza at
Tel: 03-2920297. The deadline for entries is July 27. The award
presentation will be held at the Pikom annual dinner on Nov 26.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
