<SLUG> PLUS-OFFERS-PROJECTOR sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Plus offers projector with DLP technology, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws PLUS-OFFERS-PROJECTOR sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   US-BASED Plus Corp has introduced into the local market its
latest projector which features digital light processing (DLP)
projection technology with the aim of providing more quality
display.
	   According to the company, the PLUS UP-800 projector also
incorporates a proprietary optical engine which features a
spherical surface lens that delivers a higher level of brightness,
resolution, focus and colour uniformity compared to other
projectors.
	   The optical engine is designed to enhance the amount and quality
of light generated to recreate an image in a DLP projector,
delivering 100 per cent reproduction of the original information
100 per cent of the time.
	   Plus said the projector is able to deliver bright colours and
clear image of any liquid crystal display (LCD) and DLP projector
weighing under 4.5 kilograms. DLP is a reflective technology which
increases the amount of light that gets from the lamp to the screen
compared to other display technologies.
	   According to Plus, the new digital projector is the first
ultra-portable projector of its kind to deliver 600 ANSI lumens of
brightness packaged in the size of a notebook personal computer
(PC).
	   The product is a super video graphics array (SVGA) with 800 by
600 pixels resolution projector with the ability to process XGA
data using intelligent compression technology. This new technology
allows the compressed signal to be projected in its entirety
without the usual loss of lines of resolution associated with
signal compression.
	   Furthermore, using innovative intelligent expansion technology,
both video graphics array (VGA) and video signals are projected at
a full raster. Plus said. It added that this means that the VGA and
video images will automatically be expanded to fill the entire
screen.
	   The projector also features a digital zoom function or focus
lens of up to 400 per cent, a 1,000-hour user replaceable metal
halide lamp, a contrast ratio 180:1, 24-bit, 16.7 million colour
reproduction, a multi-lingual text menu display, a full function
wireless remote control and a soft-carrying case.
	   The entire projector measures 9.25 inches in width, 12.2in in
length and 3.85in in height. Targeted at travelling executives, the
new digital projector is now available at RM22,500 from local
distributor Eastern Office Machines Sdn Bhd (EOM) and its channel
of dealers and resellers.
	   EOM expects to sell between 2,000 and 2,200 units of the Plus
UP-800 projector this year.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
