w1155  wstm-
r w     TO-THINE-OWN-CARsked     06-01 0749
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> TO-THINE-OWN-CAR sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
To thine own car be true, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws TO-THINE-OWN-CAR sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   I HAVE decided - for better or worse - to stay true to my Fiat.
	   True, my trusty Fiat has overheated in the midst of the traffic
crawl along Jalan Tun Razak in the middle of the day, with
everybody gawking and no one stopping to help.
	   It's true to say that my sentimental junk has a worse medical
condition than me and has to meet its doctor (mechanic) more often
than I have to see mine. And every time I bring it in for minor
repairs, I might just have to forego the new clothes that I
intended to buy that month.
	   My 18-year-old junk is inclined to break down in the middle of
the night along a road where there are no public phones and no
passing vehicles for hours. And I dare not drive it into the Lake
Club and park it outside for fear that I might be accused of
depriving others with their Mercedes and BMWs of a parking spot.
	   True that even if I started carpooling, others might still
insist on taking the bus or even prefer to walk.
	   And whenever I am driving my trusty Mirafiori 131 on the left
lane, I get honked at for no reason whatsoever.
	   My nephew Siji has never tired of reminding me that the car
should be thrown into some disused mining pool but then I do not
have to burn a hole in my pocket every month when the car loan
sharks come to collect their monthly dues.
	   In this economic hardship era, when the interest rates of all
the car loans have gone up, I can smile and console myself that I
would not be affected at all as my car belongs to me a hundred per
cent.
	   While others have to be careful with their spending, I would
still be able to afford to gorge on cheesecakes and chocolates and
give others a treat once in a while.
	   Besides, my car would be the only one of its kind running on the
road in a major traffic jam and might even be sought after in 20
years to come.
	   And when cars are crawling along Jalan Tun Razak in the middle
of the scorching afternoon and a brand new car decides to stall
(which I have seen numerous times), I can hold my head up high (and
if I could, I would even raise the two front wheels like they do
with BMX bicycles!) and drive past in style. And all sensible
drivers will say - see that trusty Fiat go! If I ever knock into or
get knocked into by a brand new car, my first worry would not be
``What happened to my car?'' but the question would be more of
``How bad is his or her car?''
	   And when I go to any of the mechanics in town, they would fix
the dent or restart it for me at the most minimal price or even for
free, for fear that I might not be able to afford the bill.
	   Now whenever the car decides to stall, I would curse it and
threaten to throw it into the disused mining pool in Puchong but
the silver lining here is that when it is repaired and on the road
again, I will be a stronger person having gone through that phase.
	   And if I ever decide to stop to buy those things that they sell
at the roadside stalls along the highways, the sellers would not
even think of charging me more than the usual price. They might
even reduce it if I asked them.
	   I know that my ``fiatty'' Fiat is at present out of fashion but
then again, the fact remains that a child developing a hand at art
would definitely start off by drawing MY car, and not some sporty
sedan.
	   And when senior journalists talk about the old times when they
were driving only Peugeots and Fiats, I can join in and say ``Look,
I am going down the same road as you people''. There will also come
a day when I can talk of ``Those days when .....'' to the younger
breed.
	   While for many people Fiat stands for ``Fiat Is Always
Trouble'', to me, MY Fiat stands for ``Fiat Is Always True''.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
(PROFILE
(WS SL:TO-THINE-OWN-CAR sked; CT:w; 
(REG:ENGL;)
(LANG:ENGLISH;))
