r w     BOOST-CPU'S-PERFORMANCEs     06-01 0535
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BOOST-CPU'S-PERFORMANCE sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
HyperRace MxPro 180 to boost CPU's performance, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws BOOST-CPU'S-PERFORMANCE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   HYPERTEC Memory (M) Sdn Bhd, which specialises in personal
computer (PC) memory, has announced the availability of the
HyperRace MxPro 180, a processor upgrade designed to enhance
central processing unit (CPU) performance by up to 360 per cent.
	   According to the company, the HyperRace MxPro 180 is able to
enhance CPU performance up to 360 per cent and is one of the most
cost-effective MMX upgrade products, allowing users to run
MMX-enabled software.
	   Hypertec Memory said the product could be easily installed and
it provides a simple alternative to buying a new Pentium MMX
computer.
	   ``The HyperRace MxPro 180 will bring an organisation or an
individual's existing system up to today's expected performance
standard for a fraction of the cost of a new Pentium PC,'' said
Hypertec Malaysia's managing director Colin Lillywhite at the
product launch held in conjunction with the opening of the local
office.
	   ``The local offices provide benefits for customers in this
region by giving them reliable and fast delivery of our large,
quality product range, including HyperRace processor upgrades and
HyperRam memory products,'' he said.
	   The company said the HyperRace MxPro 180 is suitable for users
of Windows 95, Windows NT, games software and Internet
applications. It is capable of increasing the software performance
on a 75-megahertz (MHz) Pentium processor by 47 per cent for
Windows 95, 41 per cent for Windows NT and by 368 per cent for
multimedia and games programs.
	   The HyperRace MxPro 180's socket-5 and socket-7 and basic input
output system (BIOS) enhancement software ensures compatibility
with existing systems. The product, said Hypertec Memory, meets the
standards of XXCAL Inc, an American independent testing body that
provides quality assurance and compatibility testing, and the
Australian Electromagnetic Interference Standard (C-Tick).
	   It also allows users to take full advantage of the increased
internal CPU speed of 180MHz by including a large 64K internal
write-back cache memory. The size of this cache memory reduces the
number of external accesses which the CPU has to make. Hypertec
Memory claimed this is significant as Pentium-class CPUs slow down
between 50 and 66MHz when accessing the rest of the system.
	   The HyperRace MxPro 180 is available at a retail price of RM599.
	   
</TEXT>
