<TEXT>
	   ALL business operators involved in the food industry will be
required to attend a mandatory food handling course conducted by
the Selayang Municipal Council.
	   Council president Kasjoo Kadis said the certificate course would
be a requirement for food outlet operators, in both restaurants and
hawker centres, in obtaining licences to operate.
	   He said the day-long course, which will cost RM65 per person,
was crucial in view of the current cholera situation and water
shortage which called for special emphasis on cleanliness.
	   Asked if existing licence holders also needed to attend the
course, Kasjoo said attending the course would be a criteria in the
renewal of licences.
	   He said the course, which started in 1996, was an on-going
activity.
	   
