<SLUG> BC-Russia-Afghan Quake </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russia expresses regret over earthquake in Afghanistan 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ The Russian Foreign Ministry expressed ``deep
regret'' Monday over a 6.9-magnitude earthquake that killed
thousands in neighboring Afghanistan and said it would consider
sending humanitarian aid.
	   The quake, which hit Saturday, is ``the latest natural
catastrophe which occurred in the long-suffering Afghanistan,''
Foreign Ministry spokesman Valery Nesterushkin told the Interfax
news agency.
	   Russia has previously contributed helicopters and other
transportation devices for rescue and relief efforts.
	   (ls) 	   
