w1189  wstm-
r w     LEGEND-OFFERS-LATESTsked     06-01 0437
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> LEGEND-OFFERS-LATEST sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Legend offers latest Brilliant motherboards, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws LEGEND-OFFERS-LATEST sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   LEGEND QDI has announced the latest Brilliant Series
motherboards which the company said incorporates Intel's latest
Pentium II class 440BX accelerator graphics port (AGP) set and
attains the PC100 technological edge.
	   Its first two models - Brilliant I and Brilliant IV - are the
first generation of Legend QDI's motherboards to meet PC100's
specifications, which according to the company is recognised as the
industry standard for personal computer (PC) architecture.
	   The motherboards help boost the performance of systems running
on 100 megahertz (MHz) and support substantial data throughput for
three-dimensional (3-D) and multimedia applications. Legend QDI
said the 440BX motherboard is the first solution to realise this
concept (which it expects to be the mainstream of the computer
industry in the next decade) in the marketplace.
	   The BX motherboard is capable of running at 100MHz front side
bus (FSB), a technology which will restrict bottlenecks from
prevailing 66MHz system clock frequency.
	   Legend QDI said the new BX platform increases the overall
performance of the system significantly by running the system clock
from 66 up to 100MHz.
	   Besides supporting a 100MHz system bus speed, the 440BX
motherboard is capable of supporting 100MHz synchronous dynamic
random access memory (SDRAM).
	   The AGP performance is also optimised with the increase in SDRAM
bus speed. Compared to the LX platform, AGP's new architecture and
its ability to store 3-D texture data in the main memory at 100MHz
bus speed can be ascertained under the BX platform, according to
Legend QDI.
	   Other features in the Brilliant series are SpeedEasy
(jumper-free for CPU speed setting), PowerEasy (a tool for
upgrading) and LogoEasy (logo utility).
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
