<HEADLINE>
Gebrselassie sets new men's 10,000-meter record 
</HEADLINE>
URGENT
<TEXT>
	   HENGELO, Netherlands (AP) _ Ethiopian Haile Gebrselassie
bettered the men's 10,000 meter world record by five seconds Monday
finishing in 26 minutes 22.77 seconds at the Adriaan Paulen
Memorial track.
	   He shattered the nine-month old mark of 26:27.85 set by Kenyan
Paul Tergat in Brussels on August 27 last year.
	   Gebreselassie ran the last nine laps of the track with only
lapped runners for company after the last of the five Ethiopian
pacemakers he'd brought along dropped out.
	   The Ethiopian clocked a half-way split time of 13:11.53 over the
first five kilometers.
