<HEADLINE>
Russian helicopter crashes in Antarctic, 5 killed 35 minutes. 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: UPDATES with new 3rd graf, ship arrived at crash site within
<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A Russian helicopter crashed in the Antarctic,
killing five people and seriously injuring four, Russian news
agencies reported.
	   The MI-8 helicopter with nine people on board crashed 15 minutes
after taking off from the Russian research vessel Academician
Fyodorov and shortly before reaching its destination, the Russian
Antarctic station Novolazarevskaya.
	   Crew members on the bridge of the Academician Fyodorov saw the
aircraft crash, and the vessel arrived at the scene with medics and
first within 35 minutes, the ITAR-Tass news agency said.
	   The news agency said the four injured people were taken to the
ship in grave condition. Those killed included three crew members
and two members of the Russian Antarctic expedition.
	   (ls/jai) 	   
