<HEADLINE>
Report: Kurdish rebels kill 18 Turkish soldiers in southeast 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   ANKARA, Turkey (AP) _ Kurdish rebels killed 18 Turkish soldiers
and 14 pro-government village guards in fighting in southeastern
Turkey, a Kurdish news agency reported.
	   The Germany-based DEM news agency said the soldiers died when
rebels ambushed a military convoy in the province of Diyarbakir.
	   The village guards were killed in clashes in the provinces of
Sirnak and Martin, DEM said. Turkey's Anatolia news agency said 10
village guards had been killed near Sirnak.
	   Several thousand village guards are fighting along with the
Turkish army against the autonomy-seeking rebels.
	   According to official estimates, 37,000 people have been killed
in the conflict since 1984.
