<TEXT>
	   22, 1996 - Detained at the Brisbane International Airport after
failing to declare more than A$1.2 million (RM2.9 million) when he
was leaving Australia for New Zealand.
	   Dec 24, 1996 - Charged in Brisbane magistrate's court.
	   Dec 31, 1996 - Claimed that the money belonged to his brothers.
	   April 14, 1997 - Resigned as Selangor Menteri Besar, State Umno
liaison chief, Barisan Nasional chairman for Selangor and Federal
Territory but remained as Umno vice-president and State Assemblyman
for Batang Kali.
	   May 10, 1997 - Exempted from all Umno supreme council meetings
and ceased to function as Umno vice-president.
	   Aug 19, 1997 - The Brisbane magistrate's court committed
Muhammad to stand trial in the Brisbane District Court.
	   May 19, 1998 - Muhammad's trial at the District Court began.
	   May 29, 1998 - Acquitted.
	   
