<TEXT>
	   TELUK INTAN, Sun. - Anyone who possesses the commitment and
capability to ensure continuity in Wanita Umno's struggle can lead
the movement, said its chief Datuk Dr Siti Zaharah Sulaiman.
	   The movement had no intention of imposing a no-contest rule for
the chief post in next year's elections.
	   ``I am ready to be challenged but whoever is seeking election to
the post must ensure continuity in the movement's struggle,'' she
said yesterday.
	   Siti Zaharah hoped delegates at the coming general assembly
would not pass a resolution calling for no-contest for the post.
	   She said the movement had embarked on a programme to encourage
members to diversify economic activities to help improve the
country's economic health.
	   These included encouraging savings in Amanah Saham Wanita and
involvement in co-operatives, and conducting courses on
agriculture-based processing.
	   She said the assistance of two ministries and the Malaysian
Agricultural Research Development Institute had been sought to
realise the programme.
	   
