<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - Against the background of the present
economic slowdown, Esso Malaysia Bhd is offering a reduction of
three sen per litre in the prices of both regular and unleaded Esso
Xtreme petrol from today until June 14.
	   The promotion will be in all Esso service stations in Malaysia.
	   Esso chairman and chief executive officer Datuk Philip Dingle
said in a statement today the promotion was mooted as ``all
Malaysians deserve an immediate benefit by getting reduced petrol
prices''.
	   ``In these difficult times, all Malaysian drivers need a
break,'' he said.
	   He said the public responded strongly to Esso Xtreme fuel as
well as to purchasing in Esso's convenient stores, Tiger Marts.
	   ``We want to continue to support our customers by not only
giving them the best quality products and services, but an extra
bonus of cheaper petrol.''
	   He said Esso wanted to do something positive for its consumers
by reducing the prices although many neighbouring countries have
been required to raise fuel prices at these times.
	   
</TEXT>
