Shares expected to be under pressure, BUSINESS TIMES  
   xfdws SHARES-UNDER-PRESSURE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   SHARE prices are expected to remain under pressure this week as
regional economic concerns weigh on the market, dealers said last
Friday.
	   The benchmark Straits Times Industrials index of the Stock
Exchange of Singapore fell 58.74 points or 4.5 per cent to close
the week at 1,254.93 last Friday.
	   ``The market will remain under pressure amid fears that more
depressing economic numbers will emerge in the region,'' a dealer
with a local stock brokerage said.
	   Average daily turnover fell to 94.01 million shares worth
S$168.23 million from 202.53 million shares valued at S$318.50
million the previous week.
	   The hottest stock for the week was Singapore Telecommunications
Ltd, with 32.09 million shares traded.
	   The top gainer was Singapore Technology Industrial Corp, rising
13 cents to S$1.66 while the biggest loser was Creative Technology
Ltd, falling S$3.00 to S$30.50.
	   
