MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Malaysian Oxygen Bhd, BUSINESS TIMES  
   xfdws MALAYSIAN-OXYGEN-BHD sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   BUSINESS TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   MALAYSIAN Oxygen Bhd (MOX) reported a 5.6 per cent lower group
pre-tax profit of RM40.15 million for the six months ended March 31
1998 compared with RM42.52 million in the previous corresponding
period.
	   This was achieved on a RM193.66 million turnover, marginally
lower than the RM194.66 million previously.
	   MOX said the Government's revised gross domestic product growth
together with measures taken to stabilise and revive the economy
will continue to have an impact on current trading conditions.
	   It anticipates that demand from the petrochemical, oleochemical
and electronic sectors will continue to grow while that of
metalworks is expected to level off with the slowdown in the
construction industry.
	   Earnings per MOX share during the period stood at 26.6 sen
against 25.6 sen previously.
	   Directors have declared a first gross interim dividend of 8.1
sen, to be paid to shareholders on July 3 1998.
	   
