<TEXT>
	   PENANG, Sun. - The DAP yesterday called for Parliament to
convene an emergency meeting to debate the negative gross domestic
product growth of 1.8 per cent in the first quarter of this year.
	   Its secretary-general Lim Kit Siang also called on the National
Economic Action Council to justify its failure in effecting
economic recovery and for not preparing Malaysians for the prospect
of a GDP contraction.
	   ``The worst fears about the Malaysian economic crisis have now
been confirmed,'' Lim said.
	   He was speaking at the ``Sympathy, Support and Solidarity with
Lim Guan Eng'' ceramah at Bukit Mertajam.
	   ``Bank Negara today announced that 1998's first quarter GDP was
-1.8 per cent, the first decline in 13 years.''
	   ``Bank Negara also said non-performing loans rose to 10.6 per
cent in April from 6.7 per cent in December, 1997.''
	   ``In absolute terms, NPLs increased from RM28.3 billion in
December 1997 to RM44.3 billion in April,'' he added.
	   ``With such bad news, I fear for the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange
when it opens on Monday and I hope that it will not register a new
low in the 11-month economic crisis in the coming week.''
	   
