<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
People urged to unite and give their full support, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws PEOPLE-URGED-TO-UNITE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KOTA BARU, Fri. - Former Deputy Prime Minister Tun Ghafar Baba
urged the people to unite and give their full support to the
Government in its efforts to overcome the economic problems
besetting the country.
	   ``This is the time for the people to show their love for the
country and by being united and giving support to the Government in
its measures to overcome the problem. We may be able to expedite
the nation's economic recovery,'' he said after meeting Umno
members last night.
	   He was here as part of his nationwide tour to explain to Umno
members about the economic slowdown.
	   Ghafar likened the economic problems to a house on fire.
	   ``Hence, as the occupants of the house, we should help to put
out the flames instead of pointing fingers at one another as this
can worsen the situation and may lead to political instability,''
he added.
	   He said the people should not be worried as efforts were being
made to ensure the recovery of the country's economy.
	   ``The people should help by reducing their expenditure,
especially on vegetables, by planting them,'' he added.
	   He also expressed the need for the people to understand the
reasons for the assistance given by the Government to Bumiputera
companies facing financial problems following the economic
slowdown.
	   ``It is not to help individuals or the owners of the companies
concerned,'' he said, adding that the Government only assisted
companies which can bring revenue to the Government.
	   ``The Government helps these companies because they bring
foreign exchange to the country.''
	   
</TEXT>
