</HEADLINE>
Lawyer gets RM135,000 over dismissal, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws LAWYER-GETS-DISMISSAL sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - A lawyer, who brought an action against a
legal firm for wrongful dismissal two year ago, was awarded
RM135,000 in back wages and compensation by the Industrial Court.
	   Industrial Court chairman Abu Hashim Abu Bakar, in ordering the
Johor Baru-based legal firm of Gary Yuen  Tan to pay Diana Ann
Seah RM120,000 in backwages and RM15,000 as compensation for loss
of employment, said to reinstate her would not be conducive to a
healthy working environment for both the parties.
	   In his judgment, handed down on May 20 and made available to the
Press today, he said the firm had failed to hold a domestic inquiry
before terminating the services of Diana.
	   He said she was was not given the chance to redeem herself of
the charges brought by the firm during the hearing stage on why she
was dismissed.
	   ``As a company, being a firm of advocates and solicitors at
that, how could it have blundered on this basic duty of due
enquiry?'' he asked.
	   Diana had claimed she commenced her employment with the firm in
April, 1995, with a salary of RM5,000 per month until she was
terminated without any explanation on March 31, 1996.
	   The firm had alleged at the hearing that among the reasons for
it to dismiss Diana was that she had been dishonest, misrepresented
the firm, was habitually late and gave wrong advice to clients.
	   
</TEXT>
