INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Sun. - Singer Siti Nurhaliza, pop group BM Boys
and Malaysia's own James Bond girl Michelle Yeoh called on
Malaysians to stand united in facing the country's economic
problems.
	   They were among celebrities at the Semarakkan Semangat Cinta
Malaysia concert organised by the MCA at Dataran Merdeka tonight.
	   Organised as part of the MCA's Love Malaysia, Buy Malaysian
Goods campaign, the concert was aimed at promoting unity and
patriotism, as well as spurring Malaysians to help revitalise the
country's economy by buying local goods.
	   Prime Minister Datuk Seri Dr Mahathir Mohamad, who was
accompanied by his wife Datin Seri Dr Siti Hasmah Mohd Ali, was the
guest of honour at the open-air concert.
	   MCA president Datuk Seri Dr Ling Liong Sik said the campaign was
enjoying ``encouraging'' support from Malaysians of all walks of
life.
	   ``With united support from the people, we will surely be able to
meet the challenges posed by these economic problems.''
	   Present were the party's deputy president, Datuk Lim Ah Lek,
Wanita MCA chief Datuk Teng Gaik Kwan and its Youth chief Datuk
Chan Kong Choy, as well as other senior party officials.
	   
