<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
`Build confidence in Kelantan Umno', NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws BUILD-CONFIDENCE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KOTA BARU, Sun. - Umno members in Kelantan should build people's
confidence in the party and Barisan Nasional if they are to wrest
the State from Pas in the next general election.
	   State Umno deputy liaison chief Datuk Annuar Musa said the party
should be strong and united.
	   ``People have the impression that Kelantan Umno is divided. We
have to shed that image and this can be done if there is
co-operation from all party leaders and members in Kelantan.
	   ``We have to work as a team, failing which we will not get the
support from the people,'' he told reporters after opening the
Kelantan Umno Convention at Perdana Resort at Pantai Cahaya Bulan
yesterday.
	   Annuar, who is also Rural Development Minister, said Umno
divisions in the State should enlighten the people on the benefits
they would receive if the Barisan Nasional was returned to power.
	   ``The Federal Government will be able to provide more
(assistance) for the Kelantan people if Barisan Nasional is also in
power in the State,'' he said.
	   He said Pas, despite ruling Kelantan, could not do much to
develop the State.
	   ``The State Government requires Federal assistance and whenever
faced with problems, the leaders seek the Federal Government's
assistance,'' he added.
	   He also expressed regret over the attitude of the State
Government leaders for not telling the truth.
	   ``They come to us (Federal Government) for assistance, but when
they return (to Kelantan), they tell the people different things,''
he said.
	   
</TEXT>
