<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-World Cup-Norway </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Norwegian Coach: ``Brazil not as good as FIFA ranking'' 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
	   OSLO, Norway (AP) _ Brazil are a hot favorite to win their fifth
World Cup title in France, but Norwegian Coach Egil ``Drillo''
Olsen said Monday there is a chance the defending champions would
not make it to the second round.
	   ``Brazil is not as good as the FIFA ranking suggests, and it is
not unlikely that they will be beaten by two of the teams in Group
A. But I don't think that will happen,'' Olsen said.
	   Brazil tops FIFA's ranking, Norway is seventh.
	   Brazil opens the World Cup against Scotland on June 10.
	   In May 1997, Olsen's team stunned the soccer world by beating
Brazil 4-2 in Oslo.
	   Olsen's concern now is Norway's Group A opener against Morocco
on June 10.
	   ``Morocco is not going to be a push over. I was impressed when
Morocco held France to a draw. However, England was a
disappointment in their scoreless tie against Belgium,'' he said.
	   (kk/ls) 	   
</TEXT>
