Federal Court to hear bomoh couple's appeal, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws FEDERAL-COURT-TO-HEAR sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - The Federal Court will hear on June 29 the
appeal by bomoh couple Maznah Ismail and her husband Mohd Affandi
Abdul Rahman as well as their assistant Juraimi Hussain against the
Court of Appeal decision, dismissing their appeal against their
death sentence for killing a State assemblyman.
	   The Court of Appeal had dismissed their appeal on Oct 24 last
year.
	   They were convicted by the Temerloh High Court for the murder of
Batu Talam State Assemblyman Datuk Mazlan Idris four years ago.
Mazlan's body was cut up into 18 parts.
	   They are taking up their appeal to the Federal Court - their
last chance to escape the gallows - after the Court of Appeal held
that there was no substantial miscarriage of justice in the case.
	   Maznah, 41, better known as Mona Fandey, Mohd Affandi, 39, and
Juraimi, 27, were sentenced to death on Feb 9, 1995.
	   
