<BODY>
<SLUG> BOI-OFFERS-FRANCHISE sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
BOI offers franchise for oil spill products, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws BOI-OFFERS-FRANCHISE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   A PENANG-based environment research and development
multinational is offering franchise opportunities to local
companies in the various States for its waste water treatment
systems and oil spill remediation products and technology.
	   The opportunity is being offered to companies - especially
Bumiputera ones - involved in environmental protection,
engineering, health or safety.
	   BOI Technology Holding Sdn Bhd executive group managing director
and chairman Dr Lothar K. Luensmann said no franchising fee would
be imposed although a ``minimal'' royalty based on the company's
level of expertise would be charged.
	   The new system would be offered through BOI's technical
subsidiary BOI Engineering Sdn Bhd for the company's Biodegradable
Oil Interceptor (BOI) product, BOI Treatment Unit and Biological
Integrated Oil Spill Combat Tool and Recycling System.
	   ``We feel the environment issue in Malaysia is fast becoming a
crucial one which must be addressed by Malaysians and not
foreigners.
	   ``It is our opinion that the involvement of local companies is
the most effective way of transferring the latest technology and
distributing our products to strategic areas,'' he told the New
Straits Times.
	   ``The existence of fully-equipped, localised response units,
operated by trained specialists will increase each State's capacity
to respond to oil spills and provide effective treatment of oily
waste,'' added Leunsmann.
	   BOI is believed to be the first Malaysian MNC involved in
environmental issues to make this kind of offer to local companies.
	   The company was set up by a group of German and American
investors in 1995 with a paid-up capital of RM5 million.
	   It is a locally-registered holding company with four subsidaries
in research and development, environmental engineering and
manufacture of environmentally-friendly products.
	   BOI Technology director Datuk Arni Lampam said the resources
available would be mobilised in the event of a major oil spill.
	   ``The BOI equipment made available through the franchise system
is suitable to combat small and large-scale oil spills both
on-shore and off-shore, for the treatment of industrial oily waste
in compliance with ISO 14000 and Department of Environment
regulations,'' he added.
	   Interested companies can write to: BOI Technology Holding Sdn
Bhd (Attention: Business Development Committee), Suite 9.05, 9th
Floor, Menara MWE Plaza, No:8, Lebuh Farquhar, 10200 Penang,
Fax:04-2629697 or e-mail:boitech  boi.com 
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS
TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights reserved as distributed by
WorldSources, Inc. 	   
