MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Filipino singer freed of rape charge, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws FILIPINO-SINGER-FREED sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - Filipino singer Rafael M. Centenera was
acquitted by the Sessions Court today on two counts of raping a
15-year-old girl without his defence being called.
	   Judge Lim Yee Lan said there were material contradictions and
inconsistencies in the evidence given by the victim and her mother.
	   She said even if the victim was a credible witness, there was no
corroboration to support her evidence on the sexual intercourse and
identity of the accused.
	   Lim said the prosecution also failed to prove the ingredients of
the alleged offences, including the girl's age, the dates and facts
of the alleged incidents.
	   Centenera, 50, was charged with raping the girl, also a Filipino
who is now 17, at his residence in Forum Condominium Apartment,
Jalan Inai, off Jalan Tun Razak, about 4pm in June, 1996, and in
Room 503, Golden Asean Hotel, Jalan Pudu, at 12.30pm on July 10,
1996.
	   
</TEXT>
