<TEXT>
	   THE Rotaract Club of Petaling Jaya, in line with its Community
Service Programme, organised a three-day weekend excursion to
A'Famosa Resort in Malacca, recently for a group of young cancer
patients.
	   More than 20 young patients from the Oncology Units of
Universiti Hospital and the Paediatrics Institute of Kuala Lumpur
Hospital were transported to the A'Farmosa Resort at Alor Gajah,
Malacca, recently.
	   Themed the ``Golden Child Project'', the event was officially
launched by Petaling Jaya Rotary Club president Rosman Din the same
day, after the arrival of the little ones at the resort.
	   Project co-ordinator Rotarian Fabian Pereira said the excursion
was a rare opportunity for the special children to have a
pleasureable outing not normally available to them, besides
providing an opportunity for members of the Rotary International
and the medical fraternity to mingle with the children.
	   ``The children were treated to three days of fun at the resort,
which included magic shows, performances by a clown, telematches
and flag-making competitions.
	   ``The children also surprised everyone by presenting songs,
pantun and sketches. Even their parents performed and took part in
the games, to the amusement of the children,'' Pereira said.
	   Rotarians agreed that the happiness expressed by the children
will long be remembered.
	   
