<BODY>
<SLUG> E-COMMERCE-SOLUTIONS sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Lester all set with e-commerce solutions, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws E-COMMERCE-SOLUTIONS sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   LESTER Technology Group Sdn Bhd, which provides solutions for
facilitating secure electronic transactions, is ready to capitalise
on the potentially lucrative business opportunities within and
outside Malaysian shores.
	   Towards that end, Lester Technology's chairman Mirzan Mahathir
said the company is keen on working with certification
authorisation bodies for making the cyberspace a secure place to
conduct transactions.
	   According to him, Lester Technology is in a market with immense
potential, and the target users for its products range from
Internet service providers (ISPs) and financial institutions, to
brokerage firms and large conglomerates.
	   ``And the fact that our products are locally made should appeal
well to local customers, who now have more than an able alternative
to those solutions which utilise foreign technology,'' he said in
Sungei Besi last week.
	   Mirzan was speaking at a Press conference in conjunction with
the launch of the company's global headquarters at the Mines
Waterfront Business Park.
	   The event was officiated by Energy, Telecommunications and Posts
Minister Datuk Leo Moggie. Also present was Lester Technology's
group chief executive Jerry T. Wu.
	   According to Lester Technology, business opportunities for
encryption technology products would be boosted by the explosive
growth of the electronic commerce market in the Southeast Asian
region and also around the globe.
	   The company says the public key infrastructure (PKI)-driven
worldwide market is expected to be worth an estimated US$200
billion (RM760 billion) by the year 2000. By that year, the
potential market for certification authorisation in Malaysia with
national root status will be about RM194 million.
	   Lester Technology had in December last year introduced the LTG
CA suite which is an encryption technology product for complete
Internet, intranet and extranet security.
	   The suite provides public key and private key encryption needed
for identification, authorisation and authentication of electronic
transactions. Information encrypted with a particular public key
can only be decrypted with its corresponding private key.
	   The LTG CA suite supports 128-bit symmetric algorithm and
1024/2048 Public Key algorithm.
	   According to Wu, there are about 50 players worldwide which are
dealing in encryption technology products, but Lester Technology
could be among the few to offer a comprehensive product range that
includes both enterprise certification authorisation (ECA) and
secure electronic transactions (SET) certification authorisation to
fully meet the security needs of the various users of the Internet.
He added that the company is currently conducting several pilots
with one local ISP and a few other organisations, which he termed
as ``potential certification authorisation''
	   bodies. On another development, Wu said Lester Technology will
submit its application for the Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC)
status in a few weeks' time.
	   
</TEXT>
