<HEADER>
w1447  wstm-
r w     FUN-DAY-FOR-NEGRI-STATEs     06-01 0314
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> FUN-DAY-FOR-NEGRI-STATE sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Fun day for Negri State reps, senior officials and kin, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws FUN-DAY-FOR-NEGRI-STATE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   IT was a day out in the sun with lots of games and excitement
for some while others just took the opportunity to unwind at the
family day of the Negri Sembilan State Assemblymen and Senior
Government Official Wives Welfare Association (Pekerti) recently.
	   The event was officiated by Menteri Besar Tan Sri Mohamad Isa
Abdul Samad at his residence. The Mentri Besar sportingly took to
the field to join in the games.
	   In his speech, Mohamad Isa said such events served to enhance
family values and strenghten bonds between family members.
	   He said all Government departments and private organisations
should organise such events to foster closer ties.
	   Present were State Legislative Assembly Speaker Datuk Hamdan
Mohamad, State Executive Councillor Datuk Goh Siow Huat, Seremban
MP Datuk Hon Choon Kim, Chennah Assemblyman Mej (B) Lim Chen, State
Legal Advisor Mary Lim Thiam Suan, Nilai Assemblyman Peter Lai Yit
Fee, and several other Assemblymen and senior Government officials.
	   
