Shop around town to save valuable ringgit, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws SOP-AROUND-TOWN-TO-SAVE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - Prices of several items at popular
supermarkets remained unchanged since early this week. These
included Sunlight dishwashing liquid, Lux bathing soap and Maggi
tomato ketchup.
	   The best bargain for Kleenfloor was at TMC in Bangsar at
RM10.40, compared to RM12.90 at Hankyu Bangsar, RM11.89 at Wellsave
and RM11.40 at Aktif Lifestyle at The Mall.
	   Coca-Cola was RM1.99 at Giant in Subang Jaya, and at Aktif
Lifestyle at The Mall. Other supermarkets were selling it at
between RM2.15 and RM2.60.
	   Vetta spaghetti remained unavailable at many supermarkets except
Parkson Bukit Bintang and Aktif Lifestyle at The Mall.
	   In Penang, a 700ml bottle of Organics shampoo was priced at
RM17.90 at the Looking Good and Super Komtar supermarkets, and
RM16.65 at the Suiwah supermarket.
	   Suiwah, however, offers a bargain price of RM2.35 for a bar of
Lux bathing soap compared to Looking Good and Super Komtar which
tagged it at RM3.10.
	   Ekonomi Handalan detergent was RM3.70 at Suiwah but 10 sen
cheaper at Looking Good and Super Komtar.
	   Tissue paper, unavailable at Looking Good and Suiwah
supermarkets, was RM2.60 at Super Komtar.
	   In Ipoh, prices of the various items vary at the supermarkets as
some were still having their ``Maal Hijrah'' sales.
	   Shampoo and floor detergents were among the items where huge
price differences existed.
	   A 700ml container of Organics shampoo was RM18.50 at Super
Kinta, while Jaya Jusco and Ocean were selling it at RM17.90.
	   However, a two-litre container of Kleenfloor was RM10.90 at
Super Kinta; RM11.40 at Ocean and RM9.95 at Jaya Jusco.
	   For other items, the differences in price were only marginal.
	   In Johor Baru, Tops supermarket in Plaza Pelangi started its
promotional sales for certain items today.
	   Carrefour and UDA-Ocean still offered the best prices for
certain items such as toothpaste, soap and detergents.
	   Tops however offered a greater variety of products.
	   
</TEXT>
