<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ A look at Monday's play, the eighth day of the
French Open:
	   Attendance - 27,277 at Roland Garros stadium (27,058 in 1997).
	   Weather - Overcast and cool, with afternoon highs of 68 F (20
C).
	   Men's winners - Alex Corretja (14).
	   Women's winners - Jana Novotna (3), Iva Majoli (10).
	   Men's losers - Marat Safin lost to Cedric Pioline, Alberto
Berasategui (16) was beaten by Hicham Arazi.
	   Women's losers - Conchita Martinez (7), Anna Kournikova (13).
	   Tuesday's schedule - Marcelo Rios (3) meets Carlos Moya (13) and
Felix Matilla (15) faces Thomas Muster.
	   Martina Hingis (1) takes on Venus Williams (8), Lindsay
Davenport (2) meets Iva Majoli (10), Jana Novotna (3) faces Monica
Seles (6) and Arantxa Sanchez Vicario (4) plays Patty Schnyder.
	   Quote - ``No step, never in my life.'' - Marat Safin when asked
how much he has played on grass.
	   Stat of the day - It took just 12 minutes to finish the
fourth-round match between Jana Novotna and Anna Kournikova. The
match was called for darkness Sunday with Novotna leading 6-7, 6-3,
4-2. Novotna ended up winning the third set 6-3.
	   (sab/rg) 	   
