	   CRUDE palm oil physicals ended lower yesterday amid a quiet
market as the Pakistan government suspended its foreign exchange
transactions, a dealer said.
	   The development, he said would adversely affect palm oil trading
as producers were uncertain of receiving their payments in US
dollar, he added.
	   May South dropped RM40 to RM2,370 per tonne compared to RM2,410
previously.
	   Crude palm oil futures took a downturn to close easier today as
the Pakistan government suspended its foreign exchange transaction,
a dealer said.
	   Turnover declined to 2,376 lots compared to 2,664 lots on
Thursday, while open interest stood at 6,836 contracts versus 7,149
contracts previously.
	   
