<TEXT>
	   THE price on the Kuala Lumpur Tin Market fell 19 sen to close at
RM22.40 per kg on the back of weak demands from buyers, a dealer
said.
	   Three-month tin on the London Metal Exchange (LME) saw a soft
note when it was US$35 lower on Thursday, he added.
	   At the opening level of RM22.59 per kg, initial bids stood at 83
tonnes against offers of 116 tonnes. Trading was dominated by
European, Japanese and local players.
	   The premium between the KLTM and that of the LME narrowed to
US$87 from US$170 previously.
	   
</TEXT>
