<SLUG> NSTP-YIELD-DOWN-43PER sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
NSTP yield down 43per cent to RM59m, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws NSTP-YIELD-DOWN-43PER sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   THE New Straits Times Press (M) Bhd reported a group pre-tax
profit of RM59 million for the half-year ended Feb 28, down 43 per
cent from RM104.31 million in the previous corresponding period.
	   Turnover dipped six per cent to RM369.76 million from RM394.18
million.
	   At company level, pre-tax profit fell 23 per cent to RM50.17
million from RM65.08 million while turnover dropped 10 per cent to
RM240.94 million from RM268.7 million.
	   The Group said the economic slowdown had affected business and
attributed the lower turnover to cutbacks in advertising
expenditure.
	   Also, the depreciation of the ringgit against the US dollar had
resulted in higher newsprint costs.
	   The lower pre-tax profit was also a result of a substantial
reduction in contributions from associate companies.
	   The directors expect the current half-year results to be
comparable with that of the first half.
	   The group's paid-up share capital as of yesterday was RM198.33
million while earnings per share for the half-year stood at 22 sen.
	   
</TEXT>
