<SLUG> BABY-FOUND-AT-CAR-PARK sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Baby found at car park of Seremban Hospital, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws BABY-FOUND-AT-CAR-PARK sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   SEREMBAN, Sun. - A day-old baby girl, wrapped in a piece of
white cloth, was found abandoned under a mango tree at the Seremban
Hospital car park about 9.30pm on Friday.
	   According to State Welfare Committee chairman, Datuk Goh Siow
Huat, the infant, with its umbilical cord still intact, was found
by hospital staff who were alerted by the baby's cries.
	   He said that the 2.65kg baby of fair complexion was reported to
be in a satisfactory condition.
	   He added that she would be kept under observation for two to
three days.
	   ``Once the doctors are satisfied with her health, she will be
handed over to the State Welfare Department. The baby will then be
placed at the Rumah Sinar Harapan in Temiang,'' he said.
	   Meanwhile, Seremban district police chief, Assistant
Commissioner Mak Chee Onn said police were carrying out
investigation and trying to locate the infant's parents.
	   
</TEXT>
