</HEADLINE>
Illusion spectacle at mall, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws ILLUSION-SPECTACLE-MALL sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   GENTING, City of Entertainment, will present a multi-million
ringgit illusion show entitled Magic Xscape today.
	   The exclusive event will be held at the concourse floor, Sungei
Wang Plaza from 12.30pm to 1.30pm.
	   Starring in the Magic Xscape are Tim Kole and wife Jenny Lyn,
who are one of the world's top illusionists from Las Vegas.
	   Kole is also the winner of the Las Vegas Magic Show of the Year
award.
	   Having performed in over 50 States in the Unites States, as well
as over 20 countries worldwide, Kole is expected to display his
superb showmanship.
	   Wild animals will also be featured in the show, which will see
an appearance by Raja, a rare white Siberian tiger.
	   Glamorous dancers from countries around the world, such as
Sweden, South Africa, England and Australia, will add charm and
colour to the show.
	   Some of the dance numbers will be choreographed to songs by the
Spice Girls and the Men in Black movie.
	   
</TEXT>
