<TEXT>
	   SHAH ALAM, Fri. - The State Government with the co-operation of
Universiti Teknologi Malaysia will hold an international conference
and exposition on investment opportunities in Selangor in
September.
	   The conference and exposition (Incel  Exsel 98) will showcase
Selangor as the prime centre for high technology and its efforts to
cut a balance between nature and development.
	   The five-day event, to be held at the Putra World Trade Centre
in Kuala Lumpur from Sept 8, will focus on prospects and continuous
investment opportunities available, especially in manufacturing.
	   Menteri Besar Datuk Abu Hassan Omar when launching the event
yesterday, said the State Government hoped to attract more foreign
investors to help the State become fully industrialised by 2005.
	   ``The event will also highlight the implementation of
privatisation projects in Selangor, growth prospects in tourism,
infrastructure development and global and national economic
issues.''
	   He also said, based on the current growth rate of between four
and five per cent, Selangor was confident of achieving its target
of a per capita income above RM26,000.
	   
