<TEXT>
	   PENANG, Fri. - Penang Port Sdn Bhd will put all its five ferries
into operation from 6am on Sunday due to the closure of the Penang
Bridge for the International Penang Bridge Run.
	   The ferries will run at eight minute intervals to cope with the
increase in traffic diverted from the bridge between 4.30am and
9.30am.
	   Those wishing to travel to the mainland are advised to leave
early to avoid getting caught in a jam at the ferry terminal.
	   The Penang Bridge will be closed at both ends for five hours
from 4.30am.
	   Meanwhile, several roads on Penang island and in Seberang Prai
leading to the bridge will also be closed to traffic the same
morning.
	   The section of Jalan Sultan Azlan Shah in front of Universiti
Sains Malaysia will be closed from 3.30am to 11am.
	   Other roads in the vicinity will be closed from 4.30am to
9.30am. These include the coastal road leading to Bayan Lepas.
	   Those from the mainland and Georgetown wishing to go towards
Bayan Lepas, the airport and Bayan Baru should turn at the Jalan
Udini roundabout and travel via Jalan Yeap Chor Ee.
	   Factory bus drivers are advised to take note of the changes.
	   Motorists heading towards town from Bayan Lepas can use Jalan
Sultan Azlan Shah before turning into Jalan Sungai Dua and coming
out through Jalan Yeap Chor Ee.
	   The run is organised by the New Straits Times and Lembaga
Lebuhraya Malaysia.
	   
