<TEXT>
	   EASTIN Hotel, the brand new RM130 million first-class business
hotel located along busy Jalan Damansara, Kuala Lumpur, will hold
its soft opening on June 10.
	   The hotel's communications manager Raelene Sam said the hotel,
however, was open to invited guests and the Press as well as for
training and simulation from the end of last month.
	   She said the 18-storey hotel with 388 guestrooms and suites, and
six food and beverage outlets - Chinese and Japanese restaurants,
the Brasserie, Lobby Lounge, Poolside Terrace and a Dance Club.
	   Sam, who was formerly with Swiss Garden Hotel, said the hotel's
ballroom can accommodate 600 people while three other function
rooms can seat between 30 and 80 people each.
	   She said to complement the seminar and meeting facilities,
corporate clients could make use of the 24-hour business centre.
	   Other business facilities include a boardroom, five meeting
rooms together with rent-an-office-space including audio-visual and
video conferencing facilities.
	   ``The hotel is equipped with a comprehensive range of innovative
facilities, including executive floors with a lounge, ladies floor,
non-smoking floors, rooms for the handicapped and recreational
facilities.
	   ``Of the 388 rooms, 105 are superior rooms, 189 are deluxe
rooms, 42 are junior suites, 13 are deluxe suites, 26 executive
suites, 12 are executive suites with kitchenette and one is a
presidential suite.
	   ``In addition, we will have three executive floors with lounges
and three non-smoking floors with one handicapped-accessible
room,'' she said.
	   Among the recreational facilities are a Thalgo Sanctuary Marine
Spa, gymnasium with sauna and steambath, massage, aerobic, health
and fitness centre.
	   For more information on Eastin Hotel, call 03-9251111 or fax
03-9259999.
	   
