<SLUG> INDIAN-BOOK-AWARD sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Retired teacher receives Indian book award, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws INDIAN-BOOK-AWARD sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - A retired teacher has won an international
award for his book, An Anthology of Poems, which was selected as
the Book of the Year by the University Professors Association in
south India.
	   Murasu Nedumaran of Klang will receive the award plus a
substantial amount of cash at a ceremony in south India soon.
	   His 1,080-page book which contains a collection of 650 poems of
over 250 poets covering a century (1887-1987) plus a brief
Malaysian history, was adjudged the best among 100-odd books from
all over the world, taken for review by the association last year.
	   His book portrays the history, contemporary society, politics,
economics, education, religion, culture, arts and literature of
Malaysian Indians.
	   He has won gold medals at national level on four occasions in
poem writing competitions and was awarded gold medallion by the
Malaysian Tamil Writers Association for his literary contribution
in 1986.
	   Nedumaran, 62, who has written over 20 books on poems, dramas
and stories, said his latest book which is more like a
mini-encyclopaedia, is the result of 40 years of research.
	   Nedumaran, a father of two sons and two daughters, is currently
doing his Ph.D.
	   His award-winning book will be launched by MIC president Datuk
Seri S.
	   Samy Vellu at Wisma Tatt Khalsa, Jalan Raja Bot, at 3.30pm on
Sunday.
	   Nedumaran has been contributing scripts and songs for use by the
Schools Broadcast Division (Radio) of the Education Ministry for
language programmes over the last 30 years.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
