<HEADLINE>
Netherlands puts on powerful attacking show to crush Paraguay 
</HEADLINE>
Eds: ADDS quotes from Dutch coach in 3rd-5th grafs.
AP Photos Available
By MIKE CORDER
Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
	   EINDHOVEN, Netherlands (AP) _ The Netherlands put on a powerful
display of attacking soccer to crush Paraguay 5-1 in a clash of two
World Cup bound sides in the Philips Stadium here Monday.
	   After being criticized by coach Guus Hiddink for squandering
chances in last week's lackluster 0-0 draw with Cameroon, the Dutch
struck the target almost at will Monday.
	   ``After the Cameroon game, we needed a result like this,''
Hiddink said. ``It was important for us and for the supporters.''
	   But Hiddink said his team needed to keep its concentration in
defense even when attacking.
	   ``We gave away too many chances today,'' he said.
	   Marc Overmars, 3rd graf pvs.
