<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - The former principal of the Gurney Training
Centre of the Malaysian Association for the Blind, Chin Yee Tee,
has been appointed as the association's new executive director.
	   Chin's appointment took effect on April 9, following the
retirement of Winnie Ng, who was executive director for 30 years.
	   MAB executive officer Zakaria Osman said today Chin has vast
experience in serving the blind.
	   Chin began his involvement as a teacher in MAB's Princess
Elizabeth School for the Blind in Johor Baru before assuming the
post of GTC principal.
	   
</TEXT>
