New line-up for City Hall advisory panels, NEW STRAITS TIMES- MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws CITY-HALL-ADVISORY-PANEL sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   June 01, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KUALA Lumpur Datuk Bandar Tan Sri Kamaruzzaman Sharif announced
the new line-up for the 10 advisory committees on Saturday, with
three commitees headed by him.
	   Kamaruzzaman chairs the committee for building architecture
which comprises Datuk Ridzuan Abdul Hamid and Datuk Dr Mir
Shahariman Mir Shaharuddin.
	   He also heads the board of trustees for natural disasters with
Datuk Lee Lam Thye and Idris Zakaria as members.
	   The beautification and recreation committee is also headed by
Kamaruzzaman, who is assisted by Ridzuan, Datuk Zainal Abidin
Nordin and Datuk Azman Attar Othman.
	   City Hall director-general Datuk Noordin Abdul Razak heads the
traffic committee, assisted by Datuk Lee Lam Thye.
	   Chong Tho Chin heads the committee for hearing objections on
assessment rates while Noordin is at the helm of the committee for
budget and finance with Idris Zakaria assisting.
	   The committee for hawker management is headed by Azman Attar
while the advisory committees on the environment and anti-vandalism
are headed by Lee.
	   Ridzuan heads the audit committee.
	   
</TEXT>
