<TEXT>
	   LUMUT, Fri. - Police recovered the bodies of two baby girls in a
box which was floating in the river near the Manjung Raya building
project last night.
	   Manjung deputy police chief Deputy Superintendent Jamaluddin
Kudin said the bodies, believed to be twins, were spotted by a man
about 7.30pm.
	   Jamaluddin said the Manjung Hospital authorities informed police
that a 21-year-old woman had given birth to a pair of premature
twins about a week ago.
	   
