<SLUG> CONTEST-TO-SHOW-LOVE sked </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
Contest to show love for father, NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws CONTEST-TO-SHOW-LOVE sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Fri. - A message-writing contest is being
organised by the Sunday Mail Classifieds in conjunction with
Father's Day on June 21.
	   Entitled Dad, My Inspiration, the contest is open to the public.
	   The messages can be either a poem or a dedication in which
contestants tell their fathers how much they are appreciated.
Contestants can choose several ways of placing their entries in the
Sunday Mail Classifieds.
	   They can either place a text message or a hand-written one. A
minimum of five lines is required for the text message, which costs
RM10.50. Hand-written messages cost RM52.50.
	   There is no limit on the length of messages and can be enhanced
by graphics at an extra RM3.15.
	   ``Entries will be judged according to creativity, originality of
text and grammar,'' said Malay Mail advertisement manager Sally
Wong.
	   ``This contest is meant to emphasise family values.''
	   The contest is being sponsored by Braun Buffel (leather goods
manufacturer), Penang Parkroyal Resort and Pierre Cardin.
	   Three main prizes and 10 consolation prizes will be awarded to
the winning entries, comprising leather goods, watches, and
holidays.
	   The first prize is worth RM2,800.
	   Joanne Wong, sales executive from Lianbee Marketing (M) Sdn Bhd
which distributes Braun Buffel goods, presented some of the prizes
- a selection of leather products worth RM4,000 - at Balai Berita
today.
	   Entry forms will be published daily in The Malay Mail and the
Sunday Mail until June 14.
	   The closing date is June 17.
	   Those interested in the contest can place their entries by
calling Sunday Mail Classifieds at 03-2823888 or by fax 03-2824873.
	   Messages can also be sent by post to Dad, My Inspiration, Sunday
Mail Classifieds Ad Dept, Balai Berita, 31 Jalan Riong, 59100 Kuala
Lumpur.
	   
</TEXT>
Copyright 1998 NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES all rights
reserved as distributed by WorldSources, Inc. 	   
