<HEADLINE>
Dodgers designate Nomo for assignment AP Sports Writer 
</HEADLINE>
By JOHN NADEL
<TEXT>
	   LOS ANGELES (AP) _ Hideo Nomo's career with the Los Angeles
Dodgers came to an abrupt halt Monday when the team designated the
Japanese right-hander for assignment.
	   Nomo's agent, Don Nomura, met with Dodgers executive vice
president Fred Claire on Sunday and asked for a move to be made.
	   Nomo, who put Japan on the U.S. major league map in 1995 when he
signed a contract with the Dodgers and became an immediate star,
was just 2-7 with a 5.05 ERA this season.
	   The move removes Nomo from the Dodgers' 40-man roster
immediately. The team has 10 days to either trade the 29-year-old
right-hander or assign his contract.
