<HEADLINE>
MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
`Abide by terms to form marine parks', NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES  
   xfdws ABIDE-BY-TERMS sked
   Emerging Markets Datafile
   May 30, 1998
   NEW STRAITS TIMES-MANAGEMENT TIMES
   ENGLISH
	   COPYRIGHT 1998 BY WORLDSOURCES, INC., A JOINT VENTURE OF FDCH,
INC. AND WORLD TIMES, INC. NO PORTION OF THE MATERIALS CONTAINED
HEREIN MAY BE USED
	   IN ANY MEDIA WITHOUT ATTRIBUTION TO WORLDSOURCES, INC.
<TEXT>
	   MALACCA, Fri. - State Governments have been told to abide by the
Agriculture Ministry's guidelines when gazetting their islands as
marine parks.
	   Minister Datuk Amar Dr Sulaiman Daud said the ministry had
received many applications from the States to gazette their islands
this year.
	   ``We will only approve those which follow our guidelines to
ensure that once the islands are gazetted as marine parks, no
fishing is allowed in the two-kilometre radius around the island.''
	   He said some States dictated their own terms and conditions in
their applications.
	   ``The ministry has its own guidelines and the States must follow
them.
	   The guidelines are to make the islands a breeding ground for
fish as well as for the growth of corals.
	   ``We would like to have more marine parks. But before the island
is gazetted, we must ensure that we do not pose problems to
fishermen,'' he said, commenting on the proposal by Malacca to
gazette Pulau Besar and Tanjung Tuan as fish and coral conservation
zones.
	   
</TEXT>
